fields.title: 24-Days Upper Dolpo Trek
fields.description:
Upper Dolpo Trek is a multi-day trekking expedition from the small town of Juphal to the remote village of Saldang in Upper Dolpo, Nepal. The trek is usually undertaken between July and September. The trail goes through some of the most beautiful landscapes of Nepal. The trek takes you to the high mountains of Nepal.

For all the trekkers who have a burning passion to take their journey to the next level, there is a hidden gem in the most remote part of the world. This episode of himalayan Exploration Treks will take you on a journey of discovery as you visit this mysterious region where no one speaks any language other than a few local dialects, and the locals are the most resilient people in the world. 

A journey of discovery and reflection in the remote, high-altitude Tibetan region of Upper Dolpo, Nepal. A beautiful place where rich cultural history and spiritual tradition combine with breathtaking natural beauty.

It's an amazing walking tour by important and scenic spots at Ipanema and Copacabana lead by a musician-singer-tour guide, an all-in-one professional, playing live Bossa Nova songs and telling stories, curiosities, all about the history, the great composers and the magic behind this Brazilian music style that is Rio’s ‘trademark’. In this 3h walking tour, you’ll visit 10 different spots (Ipanema and Copacabana), such as bars, beaches and also passing by the places where the Bossa Nova music was written, played and composed. Our tour guide is an all-in-one professional as he’s also a musican and singer, playing the guitar and some other instruments along the way. You’ll get to know all about Bossa Nova, how and where it started, who were the main composers and performers, like Tom Jobim, Vinícius de Moraes, João Gilberto and others.

fields.title: Foundation Making Experience Using Sericite from Toei Town
fields.description:
【OUTLINE】
Make your perfect smooth foundation using the mineral sercite, which in Japan, can only be found in Toei Town. You can make a color that matches your skin tone. You'll participate in this experience in a cute building that is surrounded by nature. 

【HIGHLIGHTS】
In Japan, the mineral sericite, which can only be found in Toei Town, is called "miracle powder" because of its whiteness and high quality. It is a powder that is used by famous cosmetics manufacturers both in Japan and overseas. 
Make a silky smooth foundation by using sericite from Toei Town. 
Adjust the ingredients and colors according to your skin color and preferences. 
Create a foundation that does irritate your skin by leaving out preservatives and fragrances. 
Experience our unique powder foundation-making experience.

fields.title: The Munich Residenz Palace Private Tour
fields.description:
Join us to see the Munich Residenz, one of the crown jewels of Bavaria. Originally a fortified keep it was transformed into a renaissance palace by Bavaria’s rulers and over the next four centuries became one of the largest and most beautiful palaces in the world. Besided that the Residenz was also centre of Bavarian government, intrigue and power politics from 1508 to 1918 and over the centuries it has seen dukes, kings, poets, emperors and revolutionaries pass through its doors.
On your tour you will be guided through it’s glittering halls and see the magnificent art works and architectural masterpieces that the Residenz is famed for while your expert guide explains about the history of the palace, the royal family and the, sometimes, scandalous daily life at court.

captions: The collection of classical busts in the Antiquarium

The tour guides will give you a briefing and explanation about the history of the town, nature, and culture of the northern region of Costa Rica. During the tour, you will find backroads, trails in the middle of the farms, and fun moments in the 4-wheelers. You will visit the lookout point up in the hills of Monterrey, a local town with amazing views of the volcano and Fortuna valley.

After visiting the lookout points, you will enjoy and explore the Maleku´s Villa; an indigenous culture in the private village, in the middle of the jungle, including a demonstration of their culture and interaction with them.

In addition to providing a pleasant experience, we are also very flexible with our visitors, first-class equipment, everything used for the tour is 100% in order .

Your progress isn't measured by depth, but your ability to apply techniques, relaxation and adaptation to the underwater world. No exams. You will simply learn by doing in a safe and fun setting, with the supervision of experts. We have two options to select as follows.

Option A - Discover Free diving
Discover the underwater beauty in one breath and in a totally different way with no restrictive, bulky or heavy equipment.

Option B - Advanced Free diver

fields.title: Boracay Underwater Scooter
fields.description: We'll pick you where you are staying in Boracay (8 pickup slots are available) and you will be transferred to where you gonna take this interesting underwater experience. This fun water activity has been designed in such a way so that visitors who have no experience in diving can also enjoy the underwater views. The underwater scooter is tethered to a harness and is continuously filled with oxygen from a board tank when in water. Users need to wear a breathing apparatus or a wet suit while on this ride. Before going underwater, you will be given a 5-minute brief training on how to ride the scooter, how to signal when underwater and how to equalize the pressure in the ears before going into the water. So it's all under the care of experts. After the briefing, you will have this wonderful experience of encountering the precious marine life creatures.

fields.title: private tour to Medinet Habu ,Valley of Nobles , Deir el Madina with lunch
fields.description:
Get to know the history of Medinet Habu, the Valley of the Nobles, and Deir el-Medina as you explore with your own personal Egyptologist guide.

 Begin your trip with pickup from your hotel, then head to the West Bank of Luxor. 

Arrive first at Medinet Habu, where the burial temple of Ramses III can be found, one of the city's most important religious monuments.

 continue to the Tombs of the Nobles, where you can find more than 500 tombs belonging to the members of the Egyptian aristocracy. Take a look inside a number of the tombs to admire their decoration. Having been less attractive to grave robbers, these tombs tend to be much better preserved than the royal tombs.

Later, follow your guide to the final stop of the tour, Deir el-Medina, an ancient Egyptian village that was home to the artisans who worked on the tombs in the Valley of the Kings.

 At the end of the tour, you will be dropped back off at your hotel or selected location

This tour is important for every tourist coming to the Sultanate of Oman, due to the diversity of terrain and climate. Also on this tour, the traveler will see the most important mountain chains in the Sultanate of Oman and will reach the second highest peak.

fields.title: Half day Tour to El Limón Waterfall with Lunch
fields.description:
A safe, fun and unforgettable excursion, perfect for those seeking adventure and interested in experiencing one of the most beautiful natural attractions in the Dominican Republic, the El Limón waterfall. It is one of the tourist beauties located in Samaná. It is a spectacular waterfall of crystal clear waters located in the heart of the peninsula, about 300 meters above sea level.

- We will take a breath of fresh air; Examine incredible wildlife and fascinating landscapes.

- Ride a horse, penetrate the impressive country landscapes, travel the incredible landscapes until you approach the Salto El Limón waterfall. Undertake a shocking 197 foot climb.

- Let yourself be surprised by its immeasurable beauty, surrounded by a dry and nascent tropical forest, immerse yourself in a refreshing natural pool. Feel the ferocity of the crystal clear waters knocking down a remarkable waterfall.

- Experience spectacular views and photo opportunities at every turn.

fields.description:
Montaña Redonda is one of the beautiful places you have to visit in the Dominican Republic. It is located in Miches in the Municipality of the province of El Seibo, between Laguna Rincón and Laguna Redonda. It has an approximate height of 1,000 feet, has a beautiful natural landscape and a wonderful 360-degree view, which will allow you to contemplate some places such as: Bahía de Samaná, Laguna Redonda, El Limón, Miches and El Seibo.

This beautiful place is made special by its swings, which make you feel the beautiful sensation of flying, the contact with nature and not to mention the spectacular photos you can take. There you can witness different climates at the same time: you can see the rain on one side and the radiant sun on the other from a distance. and enjoy a beautiful sunset.

Next, you will leave the horses behind and cross the "El Limón river" on foot until you reach the waterfall by stairs, where you can take a pleasant and refreshing dive in a place created by nature in the most artistic way.

Then you will go to the Cayo Levantado is a tropical oasis: a small island in the middle of the ocean with turquoise waters and white sands and enjoy a delicious Dominican lunch. This is a unique complete adventure.

Thousands of humpback whales, also called Yubartas, arrive from mid-January to the end of March in the warm waters of Samaná Bay, in the north of the country, to mate or have their offspring. It is the opportunity to be able to advise these wonderful creatures in their natural habitat and enjoy a unique tourist attraction in the Caribbean.
You can eat a delicious lunch at the famous Samaná Bay Ilote El Cayo Levantado and enjoy its beautiful beach and sand.
On this tour of Punta Cana we travel to Samaná Bay where you can see the songs, romps and flutters of humpback whales.

fields.title: One Day Canopy Private Walk Adventure
fields.description: Nyungwe is located in the southwest, covering an area of 1016 km across the majestic hills of southeast Rwanda, Nyungwe National Park is the largest mountainous rain forest in central and east Africa and one of the most ancient, dating back to before the Ice Age. The forest supports over 1025 plant species and over 500 species of orchid and giant lobelia. Nyungwe also has 13 species of primates; these include chimpanzees and the Black and White Angolan colobus monkeys. It is also home to habituated species such as the Mangabeys and the Blue Monkeys. Nyungwe forest has its own Canopy. And it’s the only canopy in East Africa.

fields.title: Cappadocia : Best of Region Guided Tour

Cappadocia, which hosts many places worth seeing underground as well as above ground, is home to more than 10 underground cities ready to be explored, especially Kaymaklı and Derinkuyu. Paşabağı, which gained fame as the living space of monks who made important contributions to the people of the Christian region with their religious teachings and lifestyles centuries ago. Uçhisar Castle, which is the largest fairy chimney in the region and was used as a defense tower in its time, with its unique views. The picturesque landscapes, the most mysterious rock formations of the region that astonish those who see it, and the indispensable point of balloon flights, Love Valley.

fields.title: The Metropolitan Opera Don Carlo Ticket
fields.description:
David McVicar’s monumental production, Don Carlo - created for the Met premiere of the original French version of Verdi’s gripping drama in the 2021–22 season—returns, now sung in Italian and starring an unbeatable cast of dramatic voices. Russell Thomas, one of today’s fastest-rising tenors, takes on the title role, a Spanish nobleman caught between private passion and public duty, sharing the stage with sopranos Eleonora Buratto and Angela Meade as Elisabeth de Valois, mezzo-soprano Anita Rachvelishvili as Princess Eboli, baritone Peter Mattei as Rodrigo, bass-baritone John Relyea as the Grand Inquisitor, and bass Gu¨nther Groissbo¨ck as King Philip II. Carlo Rizzi conducts one of the repertory’s most epic works.

Sung in French with Met Titles in English, German, and Spanish.

fields.title: The Metropolitan Opera L'Elisir d'Amore Ticket
fields.description:
Donizetti’s heartwarming comedy, L'Elisir d'Amore stars some of today’s most celebrated bel canto singers as the spunky landowner and the hapless peasant in search of love. Radiant sopranos Golda Schultz and Aleksandra Kurzak alternate as Adina, trading barbs and embraces with tenors Javier Camarena and Xabier Anduaga, in his Met debut, as Nemorino. Italian maestro Michele Gamba also makes his company debut conducting Bartlett Sher’s madcap staging, which features baritones Davide Luciano and Joshua Hopkins as the swaggering Sgt. Belcore and baritone Ambrogio Maestri and bass-baritone Alex Esposito as the lovable huckster Dr. Dulcamara.

Sung in Italian with Met Titles in English, German, Italian and Spanish.

Later we will advance towards Burg Square, with a festival of architectural styles and in which the Basilica of the Sacred Heart stands out. Next, get ready to cross the mysterious Saint Boniface Bridge and then go around the church of Notre Dame de Bruges. Finally we will travel back in time to the Beginario of the city founded in 1245, to finish in the famous Minnewater or the lake of love.

Grote Markt.

Sopranos Tamara Wilson and Elena Stikhina, as the virtuous duchess Elsa, falsely accused of murder, go head-to-head with soprano Christine Goerke as the cunning sorceress Ortrud, who seeks to lay her low. Bass-baritone Evgeny Nikitin is Ortrud’s power-hungry husband, Telramund, and bass Gu¨nther Groissbo¨ck is King Heinrich.

fields.title: Skip-the-line Ticket to Palau Güell
fields.description:
Built between 1886 and 1890, this Antoni Gaudí masterpiece has all the telltale touches of genius expected of Barcelona's famous architect. Commissioned by wealthy industrialist, politician, and patron of the arts Eusebi Güell, visitors to Palau Güell can enjoy the exceptional use of light and space, and the unique and expressive designs inside one of Gaudí's earliest works in the city.

Named a UNESCO World Heritage site in 1984 (Gaudí is responsible for seven awarded sites!), the palace is less well-known compared to other Gaudí locations in Barcelona like Park Güell and Casa Mila. Your Palau Güell tickets allow you to explore a wonderful Catalan monument that contains the essence of Gaudí's later works and is fundamental to understanding his architecture.

fields.title: 7 Days Trekking by Lemosho Route with Guide
fields.description:
The Lemosho Route, along with the Northern Circuit, are considered the two most scenic trails on Kilimanjaro. Lemosho offers panoramic vistas on various sides of the mountain. Older information on the internet might state that the Lemosho Route is little used. That has not been the case for the past few years, it is now a popular itinerary. Because of the length of the route, the 8 days version is preferred, but if you do not have 8 days to commit to a Kilimanjaro trek the 7 days version is quite acceptable. 

The route approaches Mount Kilimanjaro from the west, beginning with a long drive from Moshi to Londorossi Gate. From there, the first two days are spent trekking through the rainforest to Shira Ridge. The Lemosho route crosses the entire Shira Plateau from west to east in a pleasant, relatively flat hike. Crowds are low until the route joins the Machame route near Lava Tower.

fields.title: Key West Glass Bottom Boat Day Trip from Miami
fields.description:
Miami to Key West day trip to the southernmost point of USA explore Key West and Enjoy a Dolphin excursion. As we travel to Key West enjoy the spectacular coastal scenery. We will cross 34 islands and 42 bridges on your way to Key West including the famous Seven Mile Bridge. You will have a total of 6 hours in Key West. 

Enjoy 2 hours on a Key West’s only window to the sea! Stay cool and dry as you view a stunning array of tropical marine life in air-conditioned comfort aboard Glass Bottom Boat. With windows to the sea, guests can witness the wonder of North America’s only living coral reef. Observe sea turtles, rays and fish off all kinds gliding through the crystal waters they call home.
After a day on and in the water, we’ll begin our ride back to the dock. Enjoy complimentary cold beer and chilled wine (for travelers18 years old and above) on our morning and afternoon trips.

fields.title: Miami: Key West Transfer departs from Bayside MarketPlace
fields.description:
Miami transfer to Key West from Bayside Marketplace on an air-conditioned Double Decker bus in a 4-hour drive. The bus has skylights where you can enjoy panoramic views of Miami Skyline and the Keys and we travel. We will cross 43 bridges as you travel through the Keys to Key West. Watch as you travel for the famous 31 Caribbean Islands known as the Florida Keys. See the the gulf of Mexico and the Atlantic Ocean on the coastline as you travel. Key West is the most southern point of the USA. Cuba is only 90 miles away from Key West.

Enjoy a full 6 hours to explore Key West, shop, dine and enjoy the outdoor cafes and local famous bars. This is excluding the transportation time to Key West.

fields.title: Dome of the Sanctuary of Vicoforte (CN) private tour
fields.description:
The Sanctuary of Vicoforte, dedicated to the Nativity of the Blessed Virgin Mary, is one of the main masterpieces of Piedmontese Baroque. Its dome is the largest in the world among those with an elliptical shape and is the fifth largest if we also consider domes with a circular plan (after St Peter's in the Vatican, the Pantheon in Rome, the Cathedral of Santa Maria del Fiore in Florence and the dome of Gol Gumbaz in India). 

The visit and ascent to the Sanctuary of Vicoforte allows visitors to enjoy an unforgettable experience in the heart of the work of art; along the ancient walkways reserved for the workers that lead to the top of the building, visitors will be able to reach the top of the building and enjoy a breathtaking view from the top of the dome at a height of 52 metres (266 steps). 

The Sanctuary of Vicoforte is one step away from the Langhe, 2h30 from the French Riviera and Milan and 1h30 from Genoa. 1h from Turin, the Ligurian coast, ski slopes and natural parks.

fields.title: 4 hours Moroccan Cooking Class with my Family
fields.description:
Welcome to our cooking class. A special experience in a calm neighborhood far from the chaos of the tourist zone. We will take you in an amazing tour to see the place from which we get our supplies and groceries as well as the vegetables and meat we will be cooking.
We will go home, drink a cup delicious Moroccan tea, then we will start our cooking journey in a warm, funny and full of love atmosphere.

fields.title: Mysteries of Porto: Legends, Crimes and Fantastic Stories
fields.description:
This tour reveals the dark side of Porto: a Porto full of mysteries and fantastic stories that became legends and crimes that still echoes in Porto's history today.
Or guide will tell you stories about Porto that few know, we will dig into the origins of mysterious deaths; people's revolutions; historical prisoners in the Old jail of Porto; the Inquisition; The dictatorship, and the Red Carnation Revolution. The fatalism of the tragic love stories, some part of the DNA of the Portuguese People in the beautiful scenario of the Crystal Palace Gardens. Legends about terrible love acts. The Saudade. 
Mysteries of Porto: Legends, Crimes, and Fantastic Stories will blow your mind. Join us!

fields.title: 3-Hour Typical Sardinian Menu
fields.description:
Sardinia offers fresh and local products that can be used in the kitchen to create very tasty dishes.
The host is a professional chef and you are invited to her home to enjoy dinner with her and her family.

Her cuisine is a fusion of traditional dishes from my beautiful land and the menu is adapted to the seasonality.
For next autumn/winter, you are going to enjoy a warm menu that includes soup and a typical meat course.

She will welcome you to her private home where there is a very cozy atmosphere, perfect to make new friends and share experiences.

fields.title: A 3 Days Adventure Package in Victoria Falls
fields.description:
The package offer you an opportunity to experience all the must dos in Victoria Falls. It combines the adrenalin, sightseeing and a safari to give you the best experience in Victoria Falls. The guided tour of the falls will give you and educational insight into one of the seven wonders of the Falls while the lunch at LookOut Cafe spice up the day as you enjoy good views and and good food. The sunset cruise refreshes you, while you sip on cocktails and enjoy the views of the sun fading through the twilight of an African night. 

Experience the rafting that you will never get anywhere else in the world as you raft a natural river and one of the best rivers in the world. Cap the day with a helicopter flight above the Falls and cherish the views of this landmark and its surroundings.
The Chobe day trip is the icing as you get to have an up close and personal encounter with the wild in their natural habitat.

The Tango and Folklore show starts at 9:30 p.m. until 11:00 p.m., approximately. If you choose the dinner show option, it starts at 7:30 p.m.

Moreover, visiting the marvelous scenery of the Konorchek canyons presents a significant sight of the unique nature of Kyrgyzstan. Traditional Kyrgyz lunch and dinner are included.

fields.title: One passenger-Private Helicopter Tour from Ft Lauderdale to Key Biscayne
fields.description:
We will offer you a unique experience from the moment you arrive until the end, because of our detailed oriented personalized customer service. 
We will fly from North to South through the shoreline and the bay, all around the exclusive island of Key Biscayne.
This guided tour will allow you to appreciate part of this beautiful city from a different perspective, from the buildings, mansions, and constructions, to the variety of wild-ocean life. 
If it’s your lucky day, which we know it will be, you can see dolphins, sharks, turtles, rays, manatees and more, while we are flying over the ocean, near the shoreline. You will be amazed at how closed these species can get to you when you are having fun at the beach. 
In general, flying in a helicopter generates different emotions, from facing your fears, to experiencing a high sense of amaze, gratitude, and happiness.

For 1 passenger tours, a second seat at half the price must be purchased.
The maximum weight is 285 lbs per passenger.

fields.title: Tubing across Palomino River + Hiking Tour
fields.description:
Between Santa Marta and La Guajira, there is a place that boasts nature and adventure. And we want you to know it. Come with us to Palomino. Take a motorbike. Hike across the forest and enjoy a walk by the song of birds. Gaze at the views of the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta’s surroundings. And then take your tires downstream the Palomino River and enjoy the rapids until you get to the point where it meets the Caribbean and take the motorbike back to Palomino. A perfect mix between adventure and deep chill connection with nature. 

- A short hike among nature 
- Tubing downstream the Palomino River by the rapids 
- Getting to meet the place where Palomino river meets the Caribbean Sea 
- A trip by motorbike across Palomino

fields.title: Sanctuary of Flamingos Day Tour
fields.description:
Immerse yourself in an experience like no other: meet the flamingos in their Sanctuary and sail around a salty lagoon. These animals come to this place to feed themselves with shrimp on a salty lagoon. In this tour we will take you to the Sanctuary and explain you the reason why this place is becoming important and how to take care of its fauna, especially the flamingos. You will be able to see them near you. You will also enjoy a typical lunch in Playa de Camarones. 

- Discovering the Sanctuary of Flamingos 
- Sailing around a lagoon to be near the flamingos 
- Being surrounded by the Caribbean nature 
- Enjoying a typical homemade meal 
- An authentic and new natural experience

fields.title: One Passenger-Private Ft Lauderdale to Miami Beach Helicopter Tour

Highlights include soaring over the luxurious celebrity homes of Star Island, seeing downtown Miami’s iconic landmarks from above and looking out for marine life in the ocean. Save time and fly over Miami and Fort Lauderdale on the same trip Fly in an air-conditioned helicopter with headsets to hear the pilot Chance to see aerial views of celebrity homes on Miami’s Star Island Tick off top sights such as Fort Lauderdale Beach and South Beach

You will be a historian and a paranormal investigator combing Old Town looking for evidence of who lived there. Access to equipment varies with each host perfered techniques. Bring your phone as you will use that.

You are going to the top Haunted Places in Old Town San Diego - Plus A Rarely Visited Park with Secrets - Bring Your Camera and Courage.

We will use equipment just like you see on the popular paranormal shows to make contact with the spirits of the past residents that still reside within these buildings.

Truly a ghost history tour with a on-hands paranormal twist. 

On your tour, you will go to...

 Heritage Park
 The Whaley House
 El Campo Santo Old Town's Cemetary

That and more stories of being buried alive and ghosts are reaching out to the living. Your Old Town ghost tour blends the right amount of historically accurate events, humor, and the sinister. Come along, it's absolutely dreadful...

fields.title: 4 Hour Sedona Guided Hike to Hidden Gems
fields.description:
Hi - I'm Jeff! I'm a professional landscape and commercial photographer, avid hiker, and local lover of Sedona. I know the best spots in Sedona for hiking, photography, and no crowds. I love showing people around this beautiful city and sharing more information about the history and ancient ancestors who thrived here. 

I love matching the perfect hike and experience to a group and helping create a lasting memory. Whatever you're looking to see in Sedona, I can help make it happen!

I'm an Eagle Scout, former EMT and volunteer firefighter, and CPR certified. I'm skilled in first aide and want you to feel confident that you're in good hands and will enjoy a safe hike.
fields.supplier: Jeff Poe Photography and Adventure Tours

fields.description:
Discover Vienna in a different, environmentally friendly way, then this tour is just right for you. E-scooters are now an integral part of our modern and environmentally friendly means of transport, on which the city can be explored comfortably and quickly. The trendy electric scooters will get you from one place to another quickly and are simply fun.

Wecome!

fields.title: Half-Day Morning Interactive Falconry Experience
fields.description: Our expert Falcon handler will enlighten you with detailed history and importance of Falcon in the region and intellectual information’s about Harris Hawk and Owls, aside from witnessing flying demonstration of Peregrine Falcon guests will be able to participate in a hands-on display of bird to take pictures while petting them and get to watch Harris Hawks and Owls perform Aerial tricks, guests can even get a chance to fly a Harris Hawk to their own gloves.

fields.title: Walking Tour Big five Rubens' churches (audio)
fields.description: I made a very personal and flexible audio tour, which you can do in your own pace (it is a selfguided audio tour). One of the most important figures in the history of Antwerp is Peter Paul Rubens (1577-1640), the famous master painter that brought the baroque renaissance style from Italy to Belgium. His influence has shaped the city as it is today. I will take you on a trip that anchors Rubens life in your mind. You will get to know a lot of about the legend of Antwerp. The central idea behind this tour are the five churches that connects the life and work of Rubens. It symbolizes the Rubens walk of fame. I am sure you will be amazed by the stunning pieces of art of Rubens that you will discover!

fields.title: Jaipur Half Day Tour on Open Classic/Vintage Jeep
fields.description: Our Jaipur jeep tour is a way of experiencing the whole city in a go, overlooking the city's landmarks, bazaars, old buildings, 180 degree view points, and the city's monuments. You will also experience riding on a topless/open classic/vintage jeep, it's a picture perfect tour to experience the whole city in less time.

fields.title: Chania Guided Walking Food Tour
fields.description:
Join Kelly from The Hellenic Odyssey for a guided walking tour of Chania.
Chania is known for its people, its hospitality and its produce. Join this tour to learn about the Cretan food and culture as a local not a tourist. Explore all your senses while you experience this immersive tour on foot.
Explore Chania with a local food lover on a 3 hour food walking tour, strolling leisurely through the backstreets and little-known pockets that only locals seem to know about. In between sampling Cretan specialties, you will also learn about the art of filo making and visit a traditional Kafeneio (coffee house).
Savour the taste of Crete and sample Greek coffee & Cretan bougatsa, a light lunch at an iconic Cretan eatery, while you browse and learn about the differences among Greek cakes and biscuits on display, sampling a traditional Greek dessert and drink as well as other dairy products such as local cheese and seasonal produce from passionate traders who are proud to share their knowledge.

fields.title: Seviaka Indigenous People and Tubing tour in Palomino
fields.description:
If you enjoy exploring the less known treasures of a region: you are in the right place. In this tour you will go to the Seviaka indigenous town. You will have a motorbike ride. And you will also talk to a Kogui indigenous leader who will teach you about their cosmology, customs and beliefs. Besides this cultural approach, you will enjoy a tire ride down the Palomino River and its rapids to enjoy surrounding nature in a different way. 

- A 3-hour hike among nature 
- The unique experience of learning and interacting with the indigenous of the Seviaka town 
- A trip by motorbike 
- Tubing downstream the river 
- A lesson about medicinal plants and indigenous beliefs and customs.

fields.title: Isimangaliso Wetlands, plus Hippo & Croc Boat Cruise Full Day Tour from Durban
fields.description:
The iSimangaliso Wetland Park was listed as South Africa’s first World Heritage Site in 1999 in recognition of its superlative natural beauty and unique global values.

Lake St Lucia is the highlight of the iSimangaliso Wetland Park and is renowned for its large numbers of crocodiles, hippos, pelicans, and flamingos.

Our boat cruise set sail across the vast lake for a wildlife-watching excursion and you get to admire the views from the water. Listen to the on-board commentary from the park rangers and keep your camera ready as you get the chance to admire the wild animals in their natural habitat.

The game drive gives you the opportunity to see elephants, zebras, rhinoceros, giraffes, buffaloes, kudus, and many more animals. There is also a huge range of bird species.

This is a memorable tour comprising a game drive and a boat cruise in one of the most beautiful places on earth all within the same day.

fields.title: Full Day Private Round-Trip From Marrakech To Casablanca
fields.description:
This excursion from Marrakech to Casablanca, which only takes one day, allows visitors to experience the allure of Morocco's most cosmopolitan metropolis. 

This day excursion comes complete with a knowledgeable and authorized city guide who will be delighted to show you the most noteworthy locations in the city.

This is one of our favorite day trips that take you from Marrakech to Casablanca, which is the commercial hub of Morocco. The trip will begin at your accommodation in Marrakech, regardless of where you are staying. Pickup and drop-off are both parts of the package.

Day trip highlights from Marrakech to Casablanca include:

- a visit to the Hassan II Mosque, which is the only mosque in Morocco that is accessible to people who do not practice Islam.
- Take a stroll down the Cornish of Casablanca, which is lined with up-to-date cafés, and dining establishments.
- Visit the Cathedral of the Sacred Heart.
- Explore the historic Medina in Casablanca.

fields.title: Full Day Private Tour from Vientiane to Tha Ngon and Lao Trust for Wildlife
fields.description:
This itinerary is perfect to see the 'undiscovered part of Laos', 
You get to see the National History Museum of Laos to briefly learn about the history, culture and people of Laos.

You will get to see one of the biggest markets in Vientiane called the “Dongmakkhai”market It is certainly the most authentic fresh produce market in the capital and is barely visited by foreigners.

Lunch will be served at one of the favorite places of the inhabitants of Vientiane capital, Ban Tha Ngnon! 
Local people like to come out here during the weekends to eat and drink with their family on a private boat, while navigating the Nam Ngum River. 

In the afternoon, visit the Lao Conservation Center. Laos’ first and only multi-species rescue, conservation and education.

During 1h30 an English-speaking guide will allow you to understand the dangers faced by the fauna of Laos. Return to Vientiane at the end of the afternoon.

 Return to Vientiane at the end of the afternoon.

fields.title: Cooking and Connecting with a Local in Puerto Rico
fields.description: Local Host Yeira will open her doors from the coziness of her place to share with you a taste of traditional cuisine integrating Puerto Rican and family history. She will guide you step by step on how to cook a traditional family dish rooted in her culinary experiences. After cooking you will be enjoying the creation of a delicious result in the outdoor terrace. At the end you will have not only a full stomach and recipes to share with your loves ones, but also an unforgettable experience in your heart.

fields.title: Full Day Tour Hiking in Materuni and Chemka
fields.description:
Materuni is located under the foot of Mount Kilimanjaro. Our guide will pick you up from your hotel/airport early in the morning then head to Materuni village. 

Enjoy a morning hike in the village surrounded by beautiful tropical rainforests giving you a scenic view of the city as you approach the waterfalls for a refreshing dip in the waterfall pool, if the weather allows. 

You will also get to explore the cultural heritage of the Chagga tribe through their local banana beer and coffee roasted traditionally, whereas you can join in the coffee-making process to its final. You will have your lunch and fresh fruits at Materuni after a cup of coffee. 

Next is Kikuletwa hot spring with a fantastic pool with small fish that offer free feet massage. Enjoy a few hours of relaxing, chatting, and a swim while having a beer/soft drink before heading back to your hotel or airport.

fields.title: Singapore to Johor Bahru Shopping Tour (Private)

fields.title: Nairobi National Park, David Sheldrick, Giraffe Centre Safari
fields.description:
The park has acquired the nickname ‘Kifaru Ark’, a testament to its success as a rhinoceros (kifaru in Kiswahili) sanctuary. The park is home to the world's densest concentration of black rhinos (more than 50), though even the park's strong antipoaching measures couldn't prevent poachers from killing one of the rhinos in August 2013 and then again in January 2014. They were the first such attacks in six years, and reflect the current sky-high Asian black-market price for rhino horn.

Lions and hyenas are also commonly sighted within the park; rangers at the entrance usually have updates on lion movements. You’ll need a bit of patience and a lot of luck to spot the park’s resident cheetahs and leopards. Other regularly spotted species include gazelles, warthogs, zebras, giraffes, ostriches and buffaloes.

The park’s wetland areas sustain approximately 400 bird species, which is more than in the whole of the UK.

fields.title: Cultural Safari Tour through the countryside of the Dominican Republic
fields.description:
Take a break from the hustle and bustle of Punta Cana and explore the Dominican countryside on this safari-style tour and get a taste of rural life in the Dominican Republic.

This tour is a great way to see the diverse landscape of the Dominican Republic. You can travel in an open-air safari-style vehicle, take a horseback ride in a typical ranch, then visit the largest church in the country, La Basilica Catedral Nuestra Señora de la Altagracia, to go to the Dominican market and learn all about its culture. Enjoy a delicious typical Dominican lunch and explore the Anamuya River, sugar, cocoa and coffee plantations. You will also be able to see the locals rolling cigars by hand and ending at La Playa Macao where you can take a swim and relax in these crystal clear waters.

fields.title: Monteverde Cloud Forest tour
fields.description: Costa Rica’s cloud forests – where misty fog clings to the treetops – offer a refreshingly cool retreat from the warmer, tropical areas of the country. These high-elevation forests contain 420 different kinds of orchids, ferns, and a wide assortment of mosses. The slight changes in elevation have made these areas hotbeds of wildlife diversity. Birding is especially treasured here. Nature enthusiasts travel far to spot the rare Resplendent Quetzal bird hiding amidst the trees. The Quetzal can only be found in the cloud forests of Central America.

fields.title: A 2 Day Victoria Falls - Chobe Combo
fields.description:

Spend a day in Victoria Falls, starting your day with a sunrise tour of the waterfalls. capture amazing photographs as the views of these waterfalls are mirrored by the great views of the sunrise. Visit the bridge where those who have the adrenalin courage may opt to do a 111m bungee jump. Close off your day with a sunset cruise on the Zambezi where you will enjoy seeing the incredible views of the sine fading away to the twilight of the African sky.

The next day is about a visit to Chobe National Park where you will spend the day with the wild in the reckoned Chobe National Park.
You will have a 3hour game drive, lunch for the day, and seal off the day with a much more relaxed 3hour boat safari on the Chobe River. Expect to be back in your hotel around 1800hrs.

Upon reaching the Rose-Red city of Petra, Jordan's most famous attraction, you enter the siq and explore the lost city of the Nabateans with its amazing architecture. In the afternoon depart Petra for Wadi Rum; probably the most spectacular deserts in the world. Arrive to your desert camp set in the middle of the desert where you enjoy a traditional dinner. Overnight at camp. The Next morning we explore the desert in local off-road vehicles before we depart north to the Dead Sea, reaching the Dead Sea 4 hours later. fields.description:

It's one thing to read about ancient Mayan civilizations, but it's something else entirely to witness their sheer scale and majesty with your own eyes. Chichén Itzá was one of the Mayan's largest cities, and a sacred site of pilgrimage and worship before the fateful Spanish invasion.

Surrounded by lush rainforest, you can spot exotic birds in the nature refuge and many walking trails, and even take a dip in the freshwater sinkhole in a day filled with ancient adventure and historical discovery!

The app displays directions to the starting point, and when you’re in the right place, just pop in your headphones and tap start. VoiceMap has automatic GPS playback, with turn-by-turn directions. It also works offline.

fields.title: Caral Tours + Barranca beaches by bus
fields.description:
Visiting Caral you will experience the first cradle of civilisation emerged in about 5000BC, these ancient people with bountiful food on hand in the rich ocean, rose at around the same time as five other major civilisations in the world. They built stone pyramids here, for instance, at exactly the same time that the Egyptians were building their much more famous counterparts.
If this new advanced culture was not famous for art or ceramics, it was its architecture that was its strength. The same grand pyramids and temples of worship that are still partly standing around.
You will discover this fascinating place in a private car that will pick you up from your hotel and with a bilingual guide from Lima, who will translate what the authorized guides in Caral will explan during the tour.
Then you will visit Bandurria Bandurria an early coastal fishing settlement featuring the first evidence of a ceremonial stone architecture.

Soak in the sound of classic Christmas tunes as they float through the air, stop for a photo with Annabelle the carousel horse.Watch ice skaters skate at a fully decorated outdoor rink, or join in on a favorite Canadian pastime for yourself under the twinkle of holiday cheer (skate rentals available onsite). Stop in at the Coffee Shop to warm up with a hot chocolate and gingerbread by the fire.

Fan of holiday lights? This is an experience you’ll never forget!

Remember to wear warm clothes this is outdoor activity. Highly recommend hat and gloves.

After departing the gardens we will head back to the city, viewing the lights of Victoria's neighbourhoods and city along the way.

Visit the most important of this city of Higüey, where you will learn the stories of this area, you will visit the Basilica of Our Lady of Altagracia, we will see the city and we will have a panoramic view of the municipal market, we will visit a typical ranch, where you will enjoy a delicious typical Dominican lunch and we will enjoy a swim in the Anamuya River with beautiful waters.
Then you will be able to visit some sugar cane plantations, where you will taste this beautiful plant that has a delicious flavor, and where you will learn how it is used to make rum, sugar and molasses.

At the Finish You will visit Macao beach where you can take a bath, enjoy the beautiful white sand waters, and relax on this incredible beach.

fields.title: Bald Eagles Nesting Area Tour at Skagit River
fields.description:
On this tour we will be watching bald eagles nesting and flying above the beautiful Skagit River in the foothills of the Cascade Mountain Range. From the viewing areas along the river we will be able to spot the bald eagles in their nests and see them in action hunting fish, birds, and animals. We will also learn about the bald eagles at the Skagit River Bald Eagle Interpretive Center in Rockport.
On the drive to and from Seattle we will see beautiful forests and mountains. We will visit the logging town of Arlington and drive through the Suak Suiattle Indian Tribe Reservation near the old town of Darrington.

fields.title: Green Tour of Brisbane's Prettiest Parks, Gardens and Suburbs
fields.description: This tour highlights the green parks and lush vegetation which characterizes Brisbane as a sophisticated city with a subtropical climate. Although chilly in Winter and hot and humid in Summer, Brisbane is graced with flowering vegetation all year round. From purple Jacarandas in Spring, red Poincianas in Summer, orange grevilleas in Autumn, and yellow wattles in Winter, there is always a floral and sensory delight at any time of the year. This tour visits some of Brisbane's most iconic parklands and gardens, but also provides a fantastic snapshot of the beautiful architecture of Colonial, Heritage and traditional 'Queenslander' homes. The tour will provide you with a comprehensive overview of Brisbane's prettiest places, while always staying close to the majestic Brisbane River.

captions: Entrance to JC Slaughter Falls, base of Mt Coot-tha
Art at base of cliffs, Kangaroo Point
Sandy beach at Capt Burke Park opposite CBD
Freedom sculpture at Capt Burke Park, Kangaroo Point

fields.title: Siem Reap Street Food and Angkor Wat Sunrise and Sunset
fields.description:
• You try many Cambodian authentic foods.
• Tour guide will brief the itinerary of temple tour on Day 2.
• You will arrive Angkor ground at dawn to get best spot to sit down in sort peace and enjoy to most beautiful Angkor Wat structure view.
• The temple structure is more majestic than any other time. 
• You enjoy to visit and learn its history more while the weather is cool. In day time is hotter you feel very uncomfortable to visit it because Angkor Wat ground is so big a lot of walking.
• Not as busy as in day time that most people think early in the morning is very busy.
• Best Way to avoid crowds and heat.
• You will be able to sunrise and sunset and most interesting temples of the Angkor Archaeological Park in One Day.
• You will watch the sun go down over the moat of Angkor Thom old city entrance, South gate.

fields.title: Cooking and Sewing & Jewelry Workshops in Arusha
fields.description:
WEHAF stands for Widows Encouragement & HIV/AIDS foundation. We have a passion for empowering widows, children, and victims of HIV/AIDS to cultivate better lives for themselves and their families. At WEHAF, our mission is to mobilize, motivate and advocate for these vulnerable groups in the areas of health, social justice, and economic empowerment.

You will discover how local people create products in a welcoming atmosphere. This amazing activity allows you to connect with the local community.

fields.title: Tour of the East Bank in Luxor.
fields.description: Explore Luxor From the First moment of your tour, Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you. Start your tour in east bank by visiting the Karnak Temples, its construction from the beginning of the Middle Kingdom to the Graeco Roman Kingdom. Then move to Luxor Temple. It was built by Amunhotep III in 18th Dynasty in the New Kingdom and it was completed by Ramesses II during the 19th Dynasty.

fields.description: Don’t wait on lines at the airport. A prívate and experienced driver will pick you up and safely take you to your destination

fields.title: Private Guided Quad Tour of Val d'Orcia and Montepulciano
fields.description:
This unique experience allows you to visit the most interesting places in Val d'Orcia and Montepulciano crossing country roads to admire nature and works. The departure begins and ends in my Fattoria Madonna della Querce, next to the Sanctuary of the Madonna della Querce in Montepulciano. Here I breed Cinta Senese pigs, a type of black pig with a white belt, of Tuscan origins and very ancient. We will take a short walk among the olive trees and the vineyard to get to the pigs, which are free, separated by an electric fence. We can walk with them, touch them and take pictures. Lunch is included in the experience and includes a menu with:
Bruschetta, ribollita in winter and panzanella in summer, platter with our cured meats, pecorino di Pienza cheeses with jams, cantucci and vinsanto, water, house wine, espresso coffee.

captions: Walk with the pigs of Cinta Senese

fields.title: McLaren Vale Full Day Tour
fields.description: As a small family run tour company, we aim to showcase the small family run wineries in Mclaren vale. Relax on your day as we take care of all your bookings and your tastings are included. We are flexible on where we take you on the day so if you have a favorite winery you would like to visit please let us know

fields.title: Private Camel Ride Sunset View at Wadi Rum
fields.description:
You will be able to create your own personal and authentic desert experience by riding a camle into the beautiful and breathtaking sunset in the Wadi Rum protected area. This wil be your chance to feeling of the authentic Bedouin lifestyle, as the Camel is has been and still is a major important transportation mean for us. We also call the camel the 'dester ship', as it navigates reliably even through though desert terrain.
The sunset Camel ride will start two hours before sunset, when the temperature is already fresher and the red sand and rock formation are covered in a beautiful evening sunlight. A knowladgable Bedouin owner will help you to get up on his friendly and calm Camel and he will lead your camel into the sunset, through the Wadi Rum desert valley where you will have the sun going down in front of you.

We will create a beautiful and unique desert experience during the most beautiful time of the day in the Wadi Rum protected area.

captions: Enjoy the sunset with Bedouin tea

fields.title: 5 Hours Boat Tour on Curieuse & St Pierre Island
fields.description:
Kreol Taxi Boat offers a unique way to get from Praslin to Curieuse & St Pierre Island, climb aboard the Taxi Boat at Cote D’or . With our efficient crew to assist while on board and enjoy the short scenic trip across the sparkling blue waters to the sandy shores of Curieuse Island. 

Cruise to Curieuse Island + Guide + BBQ Lunch
Disembark on the all too famous Curieuse Island and explore the fauna and flora with our experienced guide. Be inspired with incredible information about the Giant Land Tortoises and the history of the island finished off with a well deserved Island Style BBQ. 

Snorkeling at St. Pierre Island
Finish the day by discovering the underwater world at St Pierre Island where fish feeding is part of the daily activity.

fields.title: HIGHLIGHT -7 day Tour around the Galapagos Islands (1 group departure/month)
fields.description:
This tour allows you to join a small group led by a top naturalist guide, perfectly English speaker, as on cruises, but at the same time it gives you freedom to wander around the ports and have a drink watching the sunset, enjoying a stroll and souvenir shopping. Our group is of maximum 12 people. 

You are not short on activities / wildlife spotting, you can see plenty of animals such as the sea lions, marine iguanas, blue footed boobies. Our tour includes the beautiful Floreana island and a hike to the famous Post office barrel.

We include the snorkeling equipment. The tour is pretty active, we can help you book extra overnight so you can also just relax and enjoy the beach.

captions: Day 5 - ALTERNATIV TO TREKKING (with Supplement): Tunnels Cabo Rosa
Day 4: Floreana hike to Post Office Bay

fields.title: Blarney Castle, Cork City & Jameson Distillery Semi Private Tour
fields.description:
Our great adventure starts visiting one of Ireland’s greatest treasures Blarney Castle, the home of Blarney Stone also known as Stone of Eloquence. Do you know if you kiss the stone, it will give you the gift of eloquence?
Blarney Castle is more than a castle, it is a complex building divided in different parts: chapel, banqueting hall & family room, young ladies’ bedroom, the dungeon, the great hall, the kitchen…
After this visit to the castle, we will drive to Cork where we are going to enjoy a panoramic tour (we don’t stop to visit sites). You will learn the history of English Market, one of the world’s oldest municipal markets, St. Anne’s Church which is known for the famous Shandon Bells tower.
We can´t leave Cork without visiting the famous Jameson Distillery, during the tour you will be shown how whisky is made and you will be able to taste it.

Maximum 16 pax

PLEASE NOTE: WALKING INVOLVED/ depending of the timing we might change the visit orders

MISSING YOU ALREADY!!

fields.title: 8-Day Classic Private Guided Tour Of Jordan
fields.description:
Start your visit from the city of Amman, the capital of the country, immerse yourself in the mystery of the wonderful Petra, let yourself be enveloped by the mysticism of Mount Nebo, admire the mosaics of Madaba and enter the Wadi Rum desert, and then try the incredible experience of floating effortlessly on the waters of the Dead Sea.
The magic of this land will overwhelm you in a sea of emotions. Let's dress comfortably and leave for the tour of THE JORDAN CLASSIC !!
Historical and thematic itineraries, itineraries in the footsteps of artists or historical figures, itineraries in the symbolic places of Jordan's history, itineraries focused on dynasties and families whose work has characterized the territory of relevance, landscape itineraries and much more.

fields.title: Memphis Rock 'n' Roll Music Walking Tour and Sun Studio Admission
fields.description:
Memphis is known for our Blues, the birthplace of Rock 'n' Roll and Soul music. 

On your private walking tour of Beale Street, you will:

Meet your guide at the Orpheum Theatre, which is known to have some of the biggest stars perform on its stage

Find out who is responsible for bringing the blues to Memphis and see the house they lived in

Visit the hotel, once considered the finest hotel in the Mid-South and discover a tradition that has been going on there for almost 100 years

See the radio station that was the first all-black radio station in the country and hear about its impact on the Memphis music scene

Take a stroll down Beale Street and discover its hidden history, see where clubs such as The Domino Lounge are hidden in plain sight and hear about the characters that made up the area, like Robert Church and his impact on the black community of Memphis.

You will finish with a guided tour at Sun Studio, known as "The Birthplace Of Rock 'n' Roll."

captions: Beale Street The Home Of The Blues

fields.title: SIXX PAXX Theater Köln
fields.description:
Germany's hottest men's performing arts show is back, and it's bigger and better than ever. Pre-book your entry ticket to the show and come straight to the source of your fantasies at the Sartory-Saal, in Cologne.

The hottest dancers and singers are ready to wow you with their performance in a brand-new show guaranteed to leave you breathless. Let yourself be enchanted by singing and acrobatic dance moves in a full-filled night aimed to win you over.

With Europe's most coveted male performing sensation, your hottest dreams and wildest fantasies become a reality. Come with your girlfriends to make it a night to treasure in your memories. Get a seat up close for an interactive evening.

Few seats are available with Covid-19 safety regulations in place, so be one of the lucky few to be part of the steamiest show this side of the hemisphere, now hotter than ever before.

fields.title: Täuschungsmanöver - A Show of Travesty
fields.description:
Let us take you into a colorful world of deception!

In addition to a unique laser show elaborated to the last detail by drag queen performer Paula A Jackson, you will experience a great potpourri of live singing and dancing. Meet drag queens, birds of paradise, top acrobats, and comedy talent who will put their pointy beaks and tongues to work. Experience a journey of turbulent imagery and elaborate costumes.

Sassy, sexy and glamorous - with style and class - Täuschungsmanöver" presents the perfect illusion.

As Oscar Wilde said, "The ordinary gives the world its existence, the extraordinary its value."
The travesty show "Täuschungsmanöver" is extraordinary and cant be missed.

fields.title: Palm Beach Tour from Miami - Flagler's Museum + Hotel Breakers
fields.description:
We will start in the morning from a place of your residence or your cruise ship. Just over an hour drive, and we find ourselves in the town of Palm Beach, founded by the Standard Oil magnate Henry Morrison Flagler. Besides being a very picturesque place, this place has the most billionaires per capita in the world. You would understand why.

We will get acquainted with and talk about the famous attractions of Palm Beach including the Flagler's mansion built as his wedding gift for his bride in 1902. At that time the magnificent estate was proclaimed as "more wonderful than any palace in Europe. . . " It might have been as exaggeration, but the 75 rooms palace is really breathtaking.
We will visit hotel "The Breakers" which has hosted such people as Queen Elizabeth, several US Presidents and Hollywood elites, finishing at the present home of former President Trump - "Mar-a-Lago".

I hope that this would be one of the highlights of your vacation.

fields.title: 4- Days Adventure In The Northern Circuit
fields.description: Visiting Lake Manyara National Park gives an opportunity to see the lions climbing trees while in Ngorongoro the expectations of spotting the big five animals is inevitable but also the costs are affordable and a customer may be capable of having a choice of activities or amendments if necessary. Also the guest has been prepared comfortable accommodations during his or her safari

fields.title: 6-Day Private Guided Tour in Istanbul and Cappadocia
fields.description:
This 6 days of adventure encompasses two popular cities in Turkey - Istanbul and Cappadocia. Three days in Istanbul and 3 days in Cappadocia, including a domestic round trip flights between Istanbul and Cappadocia. 

You will get to explore Istanbul's famous attractions such as the Blue Mosque, Hagia Sophia, Topkapi Palace, Grand Bazaar, Galata Tower, the Bospherus Cruise, Dolmbace Palace, Ballat and Fener District and more. 
Tour days in Cappadocia will include visits to Goreme Open Air Museum, Devrent Valley , Avanos , Pasabag , Cavusin village , and the tour at the magnificent Urgup’s Fairy Chimneys, Piegon valley, Underground city of Kaymakli and Rose valley for 1 hour walking, followed by Uchisar castle, and Esentepe Panorama.

Please ensure to book your ticket 2 weeks before travel.

fields.title: Visit of a Lavender field Aix en Provence
fields.description:
Come and meet Provence! We welcome you as if you were our guests and in this sense we really want your experience to be a parenthesis of discovery and rest, in the heart of our 3 hectare lavender field.

Our family domain opens its doors every day from June 1st to August 31st.

As soon as you arrive, you will be lulled by the sound of cicadas and the sweet smell of lavender. We are keen to share with you the family history of the estate and we will explain the particularity of this flower so emblematic of the South of France. You can then freely visit the lavender field. Chileans are available to relax under the Provençal sun. We also have very pleasant shaded areas.

A snack is available every midday from 12 p.m. to 2:30 p.m. (except Sunday and Monday) based on regional, fresh and seasonal products.

Free - 12 years old

Free tour

captions: Lavender flowering period, late June/early July

fields.title: 4 Days-Mikumi Park -Udzungwa Mountains-Maasai Visit
fields.description: Explore the Best of Southern Tanzania on this memorable safari trip. Traversing the Eastern Arc Mountains, witness the ‘big-4’ and more, as well as native flora in what’s known as the ‘African Galapagos’. We work closely with the park rangers to take you to the best game drive spots and memorable photo opportunities. Be awed by the dramatic landscapes of the Mikumi and Udzungwa Mountains National Park.

fields.title: Full Day Fat Bike Glacier Tour
fields.description:
Imagine riding on 4-5 inch tires over ice and snow with the easy of walking, all while soaking in the austere beauty of the snow and ice. Glaciers are amazing, ancient formations that you must see up close to truly appreciate the awesomeness of their presence and to experience how they form and move.

This trip is a full-day, out and back trip where you can experience the joy of riding over terrain inaccessible in the summer months. Our experienced guides are focus on safety and interpretive guiding/educating, creating an environment where guests can feel safe, have fun, and focus on learning about snow, ice, glaciers, and the flora, fauna, and geology of the area.

fields.title: 5 Hours Walking Tour by Local Guide in Downtown Lima
fields.description: Enjoy a Lima’s tour experience with this original walking tour in downtown Lima and try the adventure with our local expert guides, who will involve you as a “limeño” with the peoples in the city.

fields.title: Wild Ice Skating and Fireside Picnic
fields.description:
Your breath mists the air as you glide across a frozen forest pond in a set of boots with blades for feet. The ice is clear, little bubbles trapped mid-way up to the surface unti springtime, and you can see the dark waters - and sometimes fish - beneath a comforting thickness of clear, beautiful ice. This is wild ice skating! 

Join us for a fun and relaxing time ice skating on some of our favorite local "wild ice" lakes in the Anchorage area, topped off with hot chocolate, coffee or tea and a fireside picnic! This is the perfect activity for both local and visiting families, couples, or individual travelers to experience the local flavor of Alaska's biggest city and have fun ice skating in a winter wonderland. 

Our helpful guides will teach guests to ice skate as well as give tips to more experienced skaters, teach wild ice skating + wilderness safety skills, and give an eco-tour presentation on the local flora and fauna while we enjoy a fireside picnic. 

Meet you on the ice!

fields.title: Plovdiv, Asen's Fortress and Bachkovo Monastery small group tour with pickup
fields.description:
Explore the 8000-year history of Plovdiv with ruins from the Roman times, beautiful Revival architecture and cozy restaurants in Kapana district. 

Enjoy breathtaking views from Asen’s Fortress, perched on top of a hill in the beautiful Rhodope Mountains.

Visit the second largest monastery in Bulgaria and see the miraculous icon of Virgin Mary.

Take the advantage of this small-group tour with free hotel pickup.

fields.title: Madrid: Flamenco Show at Tablao La Carmela
fields.description:
Enjoy the true art of flamenco at Tablao La Carmela. Located very close of Puerta del Sol, in the old coal cellars of the Taberna "La Carmela" was a former Convent of La Victoria, demolished in 1836 after the War of Independence. Every night the best dancers (known as bailaores) come to the Tablao La Carmela, who will make you enjoy this art in each of their shows.
If you choose the dinner option, you will be delighted with the best traditional gastronomy. With the "Picoteo Menu”, you can discover the flavours that reflects the past and present of the tablao while you enjoy the show.

fields.description:
With an included one-day pass to Wadi Mujib & Dead sea, you will not only have a guided tour but will also spend time at your leisure to focus on the sections that interest you. You will take the cantilevered walkway and follow the course of the river between the towering sandstone cliffs to the base of a large waterfall. Combined with the valley's year- round water flow from seven tributaries, Experience the best buoyance this side of outer space with time for your small group to effortlessly float in the super-salty water of the Dead Sea.

Moreover All of Our friendly chauffeurs are locals, and are happy to share their insights or give tips on what to do at your destination, from ancient ruins to natural wonders, we bring you door-to-door with no surprises.

fields.title: Negril Private Day Tour
fields.description:
Experience paradise and see Jamaica like never before with Deano’s Jamaica Tours. Whether you’re looking to see the sights or get off the beaten track, our guides ensure you leave Jamaica with memories that last a lifetime. 

Our Negril Day Trip allows you to see the best Negril has to offer and will give you a day you never forget.

captions: Best in the West Jerk Chicken

fields.title: Full-Day Private Tour in Luang Prabang with Vintage Jeep
fields.description:
This will be an unforgettable day for you and your friends and family.
Ride in style! This trip lets you visit Luang Prabang in an all exclusive vintage jeep!

First visits off the day are Wat Aham & Wat Visoun, the oldest temples in the city. That Mak Mo (shaped like a watermelon) was built in 1504 and restored by Henri Mouhot (famous for his restoration work in Angkor). The old part of the city sits on a Peninsula between the Mekong and Nam Khan rivers and it
contains many old temples. 

Wat Xieng Thong is certainly one of the most beautiful and sits at the northern end of the peninsula. 

As you pass from temple to temple, you have the chance to see the local people going about their daily lives.

In the afternoon, you continue to explore the city's narrow streets with their mix of colonial style houses and green spaces dominated by palm trees and at the end of the afternoon you'll have the option to climb to the top of Mount Phousi for the unmissable sunset.

fields.title: Sound and Light Shows In The Pyramids
fields.description:
ENJOY With Us By Best 45 Minutes you have Ever Seen In Egypt 
When you Book Us We Will Pick up you At 6 pm To Be In The Shows At 7 Pm 
You Will Enjoy BY Very Interesting 45 Minutes When You see Very Remarkable light shows on the pyramids
 also You Will Listen To The Explanation Of The History Of These Great Pyramids

fields.title: Lexington and Concord Private Revolutionary War Tour
fields.description:
This half day private tour is a perfect way to visit the Revolutionary War towns of Lexington and Concord and see the site where the "shot heard round the world" was fired.
We'll take the same route as Paul Revere, stopping at the most significant sites along the way to give a detailed account of what and how things unfolded in April 1775. 
The travel time from Boston to these towns is 45 minutes each way and you'll be in one of our comfortable Honda Odyssey private vehicles with an experienced, knowledgeable and licensed tour guide.

fields.title: PADI Enriched Air Nitrox Course
fields.description: We pride ourselves on setting a new standard for the dive industry. Our courses are done in small groups, with a maximum of 4 students per each Ninja Guide, so that you can have a more relaxed and fun experience. The Cairngorm National Park is a little piece of Arctic plateau and contains many of the highest mountains in the Highlands. The area is full of fascinating geology and history and is home to many rare plant and animal species. Explore the Cairngorms with us and we'll safely guide you to its highest summits and secret corners. We'll select a route that will be challenging but achievable and is big on scenery and satisfaction!

This experience is suitable for novices, travellers or anyone looking for a special experience in the local area. No prior experience of mountain walking or hiking is necessary and you'll be kept safe and encouraged every step of the way. 

Our guides hold the highest attainable qualifications in mountain leadership and are passionate about giving you the best possible experience. We are as excited guided complete beginners as we are guiding experienced hikers and we enjoy working with both the young and the young at heart.

Our experiences celebrate and share the wealth and variety that not only the Scottish rock has to offer; but also the magnificent and awe-inspiring scenery, the sense of history, the wide open spaces, the clean, fresh air and the peaceful solitude.

We guide on practically all of the most iconic and classic Scottish rock climbing routes, from the easy and accessible; to the extremely hard and the extremely remote. The variety of venues in this area means that we can select a location that will be suitable for everyone in your group. Allowing everyone the chance to explore, challenge themselves and succeed!

From total novice to seasoned pro, we promise you a great time... and epic photos!

fields.title: Private Guided Winter Mountain Walking Experience in the Cairngorms
fields.description:
Exploring the Cairngorms in winter is really special. White snow crowns the hills, clear air makes for extra special views and fewer visitors give a sense of solitude.

On this immersive experience you'll get to explore away from the crowds, learning how to safely travel over snow and ice and enjoying the Cairngorms at their most beautiful. 

This experience is suitable for novices, beginners and travellers looking for a special experience in the local area. No prior experience of winter mountain walking is necessary and you'll be kept safe and encouraged every step of the way. fields.title: Amsterdam: Small-Group Food Walking Tour of The Jordaan
fields.description:
Join this 3-hour private walking tour and learn all you need to know about the Jordaan district. Your guide will bring you to several places only known by locals. Learn about the Dutch food culture and make several stops to taste typical Dutch specialties: Pancakes, Cheese, Croquet, Dutch waffle and other treats.

The Jordaan District is known as one of the hotspots of Amsterdam where you will get to explore many of its beautiful and historical sights. Get to know all about the area's origins and how they date back to the 17th century where it was built for workers and immigrants that came to Amsterdam. 

Learn about the food culture of the Netherlands as you sample local specialties such as stroopwafel (caramel filled waffles), Gouda cheese, kroket (croquettes) and herring or kibbeling (battered, fried white fish). Get insights about the best restaurants in the city, and ask any questions you may have, such as where the locals like to eat.

fields.title: Gradara: Complete guided tour in small groups
fields.description:
Immerse yourself in a mystical and chivalrous atmosphere with our guided walk in Gradara. This perfectly preserved village has been nicknamed "Capital of the Middle Ages" because it still has intact all its defensive structures made of walls and towers that culminate in an austere but spectacular fortress.
But Gradara is also a place linked to a romantic and famous tragedy, the one of Paolo and Francesca, mentioned by the great poet Dante Alighieri in the Divine Comedy.

Among all the guided tours of Gradara that we offer, this is the most complete one that will take you to discover every corner of the village. The activity takes place in groups that can include a maximum of 10 people who, after discovering the most important corners of the village, will give you access to the main floor of the Fortress located on the top of the hill, followed by a walk on the patrol walkways, a true vantage point from Gradara's certainly unique perspective on all the surrounding valleys.

You will visit spots of Avengers, Spider man 3, Home Alone 2, Gossip Girl, Friends, Seinfeld, Romeo and Juliet, Elf, Ghostbusters and many more! 

Our professional guide will meet you with a comfortable pedicab for faster moving around the park. He will show the spots where you can imagine yourself being a part of your favorite movies and take pictures for sweetest memories.

fields.description: Watch the Pyramids Sound and Light Show, illuminated at night with a stunning audio-visual display. Learn about the history of pharaohs, the story of the Sphinx, guardian of the Giza Necropolis for over 5000 years

fields.title: Full-Day Private Hiking Tour of Kaskikot Darbar with Lunch
fields.description:
The locals of Kaskikot Durbar area are mostly Brahmin, Chhetri, Thakuri, Magar and Dalit castes. Houses in Kaskikot represent traditional Nepalese resident built of wood, rocks, and mud. You can also reach the Kaskikot Temple which is a famous spot for the pilgrims.

If you want a crowd free location where you can enjoy the warmth of nature as a short trip near the Pokhara, then Kaskikot Durbar Hiking might be your favorite destination.

fields.title: Ultimate Private Jet-Ski Experience in Malta
fields.description:
Discover the beautiful Marsascala coastline on Seadoo or Yamaha jet-skis. Enjoy an exhilarating experience with a fleet of modern jet skis.

Experience an adrenaline rush and explore the incredible natural surroundings of St. Thomas Bay, St. Peters Pool, Pretty Bay, and Marsaxlokk.

This ride is for 30-minute. We also offer 1-hour up to 3-hour tours. Enjoy jet-skiing on your own or with a friend on a 2-person jet ski.

fields.title: Full-Day Further to the Wilderness Guided Snowmobiling in Inari
fields.description:
You will see a lot of wild forests, swamps and hills maybe also wild animals.
You will experience the backwoods and their beauty.

Enjoy lunch by open fire far away from the city and roads.

The route will be decided following the conditions that day.
It is always unexpected and surprising!

fields.title: eFoil Lesson - 1 Board in Fort Lauderdale
fields.description: There is nothing truly like the feeling of foiling. The unique sensation of flying over the water is peaceful and rewarding at the same time. We are excited to share this experience with our guests, helping them go from absolute beginners to taking flight over our unique Florida waterways!

fields.title: Sentinel Dome and Taft Point from Glacier Point
fields.description: This trip meets and ends at Glacier Point (personal auto transport is necessary). After viewing the high country from Glacier Point, we embark on a 6.8 mile trek to both the summit of Sentinel Dome (8,122′) and to the Fissures and Taft Point. This route presents a more strenuous first mile while the remainder of the trip is more easy to moderate. This can be a great intro-hike for the family that includes awesome scenery, experiences, and accomplishments!

captions: Half Dome as seen from Sentinel Dome

fields.title: Full Day Trip from Cairo to Luxor
fields.description:
Get the chance to know the impressiveness of the Egyptian Pharaohs with us by visiting their imaginary temples in Luxor . begin your visit moving from your hotel in Cairo in the early morning to Cairo Airport taking the flight to Luxor. then have a heavenly daily tour at Karnak Temple, the greatest example of worship in the history, dedicated to the God Amon, his wife Mut and their son Khonsu, then to Luxor Temple to see its courtyard and the granite status of Ramses the great where you will see Avenue of sphinxes. 

*Lunch will be local restaurant

Then to Valley of The Kings, containing the masterpieces of the ancient Egyptian tombs. Then move onto Temple of Queen Hatshpsute, the only pharaonic woman who ruled ancient Egypt. Moreover, Colossi of Memnon which are tow gigantic statues representing Amenphis III ,

After completion of visits , you’ll get to Luxor airport & back to Cairo.
