fields.title: Private Day Tour Yorkshire Moor, Coast Cliff and Whitby
fields.description:
Our Tours are the only way to see Yorkshire and its beauty in a single day with complete privacy, security and comfort onboard the magnificent Mercedes Benz V Class accompanied by Andrew the guide. Andrew always places your enjoyment of the day before everything else. No other Tour in the glorious north of England focuses so much on the overall quality of each and every guests experience. We believe that your vacation is the most valuable part of your year. We respect every minute of your vacation time, our philosophy is to make every moment of your time on vacation worthwhile.

Before founding our company Andrew led a tour in another part of the UK that was ranked by TripAdvisor Travellers choice as the best tour in England and tenth best tour in the world.

Lastly and most importantly every tour guarantees the sighting of at least a couple of very woolly Sheep!

captions: Walk out on to the ancient piers of Whitby and breath easy again, the freshest air, sense of space and beauty of the ocean will make you feel truly alive again!
The giant and sublimely beautiful skies of the North York Moors National Park, England's largest county and absolutely not to be missed on any well planned visit to the UK.
Whitby is famous for many things including fish & chips & fresh sea food. It always tastes so much better when you can actually see the lobster pots!
Andrew, your guide and founder of Expedition Yorkshire. You can relax in the knowledge that he is one of the most experienced driver guides in the UK.
Guests experiencing the special beauty of Yorkshire.
Hemsley Castle or at least what's left of it. Time and war are not good for a castles health!
All our tours are onboard the technically superior Mercedes Benz V class which ensures you have a superbly safe and comfortable day.

fields.title: Full-Day Premium Boat Tour in Panama City
fields.description: The only comprehensive boat tour in Panama City - you will have the opportunity to cruise towards the entrance of the Panama Canal, stopping underneath the Bridge of the Americas. From here, you will make your way to the Grotto Verde of Taboga Island where you can swim and relax in the warm tropical waters. Cruising around the whole island you will pull into the town bay where you will depart for a tour of the Iglesia de San Pedro, 2nd oldest church in the western hemisphere. At this point is free time to hit the beach, explore the island or just relax at a restaurant. Leaving the island we cruise into the city bay for amazing photo ops with the Panama City Skyline as your backdrop.

fields.title: Private Guided Winter Mountaineering Experience in the Cairngorms
fields.description:
Winter mountaineering is an exhilarating and hands-on way to experience the Cairngorm mountains. Unlike winter climbing, mountaineering is about the journey. We'll select a route that will be challenging but achievable and is big on scenery and satisfaction!

On this immersive experience you'll get to climb one or more historic mountaineering routes; in a remote corrie, along an airy ridge or up sheer cliff face!

This experience is suitable for novices, beginners and travellers looking for a special experience in the local area. No prior experience of climbing or mountaineering is necessary and you'll be kept safe and encouraged every step of the way.

Our guides hold the highest attainable qualifications in mountaineering and climbing and are passionate about giving you the best possible experience. We love guiding complete beginners as much as we love guiding experienced climbers. We enjoy working with both the young and the young at heart... 

We look forward to exploring with you!

fields.title: Transport Service from Juan Santamaría International Airport to Jaco
fields.description: Our transport service from the Juan Santamaría International Airport or from Jaco is excellent, with the right conditions and experienced drivers, all transportation has air conditioning, we can transport more than 20 people at a time if you need it, private and personalized transportation, when you arrive we will be ready to pick you up at the airport.

fields.title: Atlantic Outlook Guided Hike up Table Mountain via Platteklip Gorge
fields.description:
Lance Kime is a world class adventure racer, spending most of his time running and hiking around the mountains of the Western Cape. Having travelled and hiked in a number of incredible places around the world Lance now lives a stones throw from Table Mountain and loves showing others the natural beauty that we are spoilt with here in Cape Town.

Lance is an experienced and qualified mountain leader, trained in First Aid and wilderness emergencies, allowing you enjoy your spectacular surroundings while in safe hands.

Drawing on our knowledge of the flora, fauna, geology, history, hidden gems and photo spots will make your trip much more memorable than simply following the trails blindly.

fields.title: Half-Day Rum and Cigar Walking Tour in Historic District
fields.description:
Panama is known for its rum, so we take you to Casco Viejo historic district to a local distillery and tasting room. From there we walk through the old cobblestone streets, stopping along the way at some unique destinations for fun facts and true stories from the past. After tasting artisanal rums we have you compare it with aged rum. All the best Panamanian rums - you will be surprised that sipping rums exist. 

Then, we will introduce you to our friends at the Habanos cigar bar to choose from their fine selection where you can smoke, sip, and enjoy before going to our final destination with views of the Panama Canal entrance and bridge of the Americas. 

Includes the rum, cigars are extra.

fields.title: Guided Walking Tour with a Native to the Trulli of Alberobello
fields.description:
A tour of the city of trulli with a native of Alberobello, as well as a licensed tour guide.

A walk through the most intimate places and customs of the city, those that only a local can reveal to you.

Along the way, you will get to know local stories and legends, customs and typical gastronomy, distinguishing historical facts from urban legends.
A 400-year journey through the history of Alberobello, to learn about the origins and why of the "most unique city in the world".

For the little ones, there is also a treasure hunt, integrated in the guided tour.

fields.title: Halong Bay Full-Day Tour From Hanoi with Activities & Cave Visit
fields.description:
Enjoying scenic driving through the Red River Delta of Northern Vietnam
Admiring stunning limestone rock formation from traditional wooden junk.
Enjoying boat cruising in the World Natural Heritage Site of Halong Bay.
Having fabulous local seafood lunch (vegetarian menu available) onboard
Swimming in the warm crystal clear water in the ambiance area of Halong.
Exploring limestone cave with gorgeous stalactites and stalagmites.

fields.title: Private Pedicab Tour of Midtown Manhattan
fields.description: Join us on this private pedicab tour which will be exclusive for your group. We are going to show you important places of midtown Manhattan.

fields.title: Private Tour Christmas Markets Merano, Vipteno and Bressanone
fields.description: With this tour we will show you how beautiful our region is, trying to convey unforgettable emotions. "History, culture, typical dishes and 100% awareness of South Tyrol" is our goal.

fields.title: Table Mountain Tickets & Tour
fields.description:
Table Mountain Tickets & Tours are Now Available! Our Table Mountain tickets service is the preferred way by travelers to summit the peak and get toured.

These skip-the-line passes get you admission to the top of the Aerial Cableway. Our guide with 30 years of experience will pick you up from your hotel and transport you through to the mountain at the best time for your journey.

At the top, enjoy snacks and drinks, while overlooking the Cape Town and Atlantic Seaboard region with landmarks like Robben Island, Soccer Stadium and more! Table Mountain Café and Restaurant is at your disposal to relax with a hot or cold drink of your choice along with some snacks we provide.

Afterwards, your guide will ensure your safe return to your hotel.

It consists of two cables, one sliding and the other independent cable for greater security of our users.

fields.title: Malta: Ultimate Kayak Adventure
fields.description:
Discover some of the most amazing natural treasures of the Maltese Islands on this daytime kayaking adventure. Escape into beautiful Maltese nature, explore natural sea caves, and swim in crystal clear waters.

Begin the trip with some tips and guidance on using the paddle from the staff. Practice your paddling near the shore until you feel more confident, and then head out on the kayak adventure.

Explore the rugged coastline and admire the views of spectacular cliffs and sea caves. Make your way to notable scenic spots such as the Munxar Window, il-Hofriet, Kalanka Bay or St Peters Pool.

captions: The Ultimate Kayak Experience in Malta
We various canoes and kayaks in different sizes.

fields.description: Locally owned and operated business, our bikes are easy step through bikes designed for the cycle tracks in our city.

fields.title: Complete Mezcal Experience in Huatulco-From plant to palate
fields.description: In this tour you will have an approach to the world of mezcal, where you will learn about the production and distillation process and the meaning of the drink in the Oaxacan community. We will give you the best tips so that you discover the flavors of this mythical drink for yourself in a tasting where we will show you the best mezcal of the house and we will surprise you with a part of Huatulco that you probably had no idea existed.

fields.title: Sunset glow tour / paddle board expserience in Miami Beach
fields.description: Experience Miami at sunset atop paddleboards equipped with LED lights on this 90-minute tour. The lights illuminate 15 feet under water and 50 feet around the board for a unique twist on this popular sunset tour. It's perfect for paddleboarders of all levels and offers a different way to view Miami's beautiful waterfront. No surfing or paddling experience is required. All the necessary paddling and safety equipment included.

fields.title: Learn How to Hydro Foil
fields.description: Wing Foiling is the art of riding a hydrofoil board while harnessing the wind’s power via a handheld wing. Our three hour course is your entry into the young sport of hydrofoiling. We also have to warn you - Wingfoiling and Hydrofoiling in general is really addictive and once hooked it will change your life in a dramatic way. Nothing beats the feeling of flying above the water ;-)

fields.title: Fatima Full-Day Private Tour from Lisbon
fields.description:
This is a full day tour dedicated to the Shrine of Fátima, one of the most important places for the cult of Virgin Mary in the world, where in 1917 She appeared to the three little shepherds.

We'll explore the most important places in the surroundings related to the appearences and you'll have time for yourself inside the Sanctuary.

During the day you'll decide where and what to lunch (not included). You can decide the departure time that best suites you.

To go and return from Fatima we'll use the highway (A1) for your convenience.

captions:
Valinhos 
House of Jacinta and Francisco

fields.description: Parasailing activity without pickup service, flight time from five to seven minutes, can fly single or double depending on weight as maximum weight to fly together is 150 K.G for safety.

fields.title: Jerusalem Day Tour and Dead Sea from Sharm El Sheikh
fields.description: After evening pickup from your hotel, reach the Dead Sea for a morning float, head to Jerusalem’s Mount of Olives for a panoramic view, and visit Bethlehem’s Church of the Nativity and souvenir stores before you enjoy a delicious meal. Tour some Jerusalem signature sights then return to Sharm for a good night’s rest.

fields.title: 10 Hours Private Tour in Saint Catherine with Lunch
fields.description:
Private tour to Saint Catherine, Included in the visit is a look inside the church of St Catherine's, which has many artworks and mosaics. In the library of the monastery (second largest only to the Vatican) there are many manuscripts and scrolls.
Then we will move to Dahab to enjoy the delicious Lunch which is taken in a restaurant in Dahab which is a small town that is so different to Sharm.

fields.title: 2-Day Cairo and Alexandria Tour with Nile Cruise Sharm Elsheikh
fields.description:
Begin with an early morning pickup from your hotel in air-conditioned transportation heading to Cairo. Once you have arrived in Cairo, visit the Egyptian Museum, then stop for lunch at the Egyptian Restaurant. See the iconic Giza Pyramids and the Great Sphinx.
Travel to the River Nile for overnight accommodation on a Nile Cruise where you can enjoy the night show with dinner and a two hours cruise along the Nile. Relax and get ready for the Alexandria trip the next day.
Take off early in the morning on the road to Alexandria. Visit old Alexandrian Romanian Museum and Alexandria Library. Enjoy a seafood lunch at a relaxing spot. See the old mosque of Abu el Abbas and the biggest church in Alexandria before traveling back to Sharm El-Sheikh.

fields.title: Cairo 2 Days Trip with Nile Cruise Pyramids&Egyptian Museum From Sharm El-Sheikh
fields.description:
Enjoy 2 days in Cairo and discover the mysteries of Ancient we will be visiting Giza Pyramids,
Egyptian Museum, and Islamic Cairo where you will explore a lot with your private guide as well as
you can try the Egyptian food if you like. Enjoy 3 hours Nile cruise sailing with dinner and party.

fields.description: Get the chance to watch the dolphins with your family, start with hotel pickup to the happy dolphin, Happy dolphin is a well known spot for dolphins to gather and play.

fields.description: Feel the flying experience by parasailing, a recreational activity where a one or two people are towed behind a boat while attached to a parachute, flying up to 40-50 meters (about 164 feet) in the air with a full 5-7 min flight time. & Enjoy the fun mixed with water at our unique amazing only twister Speed Boat in Sharm to feel the mix between speed, sun, and water.

fields.description: Unique water activity exclusive with us, 10 minutes of Twister boat, not recommended for pregnant and people with hearts problems, twist at 180 degree with high speed to feel the adrenaline rush.

fields.description: Now it's easy to book a private car from Sharm to El Nuweibaa City One Way, Air conditioned vehicle, professional drivers, book now and ask for your car details depending on how many persons!

fields.description: Take the best guided city tour in Sharm by air-conditioned vehicle driven by a professional driver. Visit the famous landmarks and shopping areas in Sharm El Sheikh, with pickup and drop-off provided.

fields.title: ATV Quad Bike & Parasailing, Camel Ride and Water Sports - Sharm El-Sheikh
fields.description:
Take part in parasailing, a recreational activity where a one or two people (maximum weight for 2 people 150 K.G) are towed behind a boat while attached to a parachute, ascending up to 40-50 meters (about 164 feet) in the air with a full 5-7 min flight time. For this activity, no training is required. Your friendly and experienced captain and crew will do all the work to ensure your comfort and safety. After Parasailing enjoy 15 minutes of Banana & Tube.

Explore the Magic of Red Sea Desert by Quad bike tour from Sharm El Sheikh. Relax, drink Bedouin tea, and experience the Bedouin lifestyle before heading back through the sand dunes to the starting point.

fields.title: Kalimera Night Club Entrance with Transfer from Sharm
fields.description: Start your evening with a free transfer from your hotel to Kalimera Beach club, Located in the heart of Sharm El Sheikh. Situated in the same place as Sharm's very first beach established since 1975! We are ready to serve you a wide choice from our International menu & delicious drinks.

fields.title: Private City Guided Tour With Seafood Lunch in Sharm El Sheikh
fields.description:
Discover the beauty of Sharm El-Sheikh with a private guide and transportation. Visit the most famous sights, like the old town and Soho Square. Enjoy a seafood lunch at Fares Restaurant.

Enjoy this amazing tour and book now!
Our team will take you to visit unforgettable places in Sharm El Sheikh.

fields.title: Private City tour, Big Mosque, Soho Square & Ice Rink - Sharm El Sheikh
fields.description: Discover the beauty of Sharm El-Sheikh with your private guide. Visit famous sights such as The Old Town, The Big Mosque, and the iconic Soho Square, and also enjoy ice skating.

fields.title: Angkor Wat Sunrise and Tonle Sap Cruise Sunset Tour
fields.description: This tour is designed to allow tourists to visit all a must-see tourists attracted places in one-day tour. Starts by visiting sunrise at Angkor Wat temple from the East gate; tourists feel like "amazing" by walking in the dark as it is early down and then eyes witness the temple when the sun rising up. Have chance to see South gate of Angkor Thom, Bayon, Terrace of Elephant and Terrace of Leper King as we driving through before moving to Ta Prohm temple. In late evening, take a boat cruise leisurely catching sunset over the Great Lake as the tour ends.

fields.title: Private Guided City Tour and Culturama Ticket - Sharm El Sheikh
fields.description: Discover the beauty of Sharm El-Sheikh with a private transfer and a private guided tour of Old Town. Enjoy a show at Culturama Historical Cinema in Soho Square.

fields.title: La Pirámide Park // EXPLORE LA YERBA CANYON
fields.description:
"La Pirámide" Park is an environmental conservation and nature tourism project with the Ejido Chavarria Viejo, it is located in the majestic Sierra Madre Occidental, right in the middle between Durango and Mazatlán, Mexico. It consists of 220 hectares in development for family, school, business experiences, between friends and singles.

Dream place to visit and enjoy nature.

fields.title: 2 Day Sahara desert tour from Fez
fields.description:
This 2-day Fes desert tour is the perfect solution for travelers who are pressed for time, but still want to experience a traditional Moroccan adventure. Set off from Fes; see the Barbary apes in Ifrane; ride a camel in the desert; and spend the night in a Berber camp. Plus, you’ll wake up on your last day to the sunrise for a great opportunity to snap some pictures. 
- See the Barbary apes in Ifrane during this 2-day Fes desert tour Ride a camel to a Berber camp for an overnight stay, and warm up by a campfire 
- Awesome opportunity for desert sunrise photos,wake up early at the Berber camp 
- Fes round-trip transport included for added convenience

fields.title: Islands & Mountains Adventure
fields.description: The Islands & Mountains Adventure is the perfect combo, which showcases the best of what Fiji has to offer, that it's not only about the sun, sand & surf but the untouched, lush vegetation where you'll discover awe-inspiring gorges & seasonal cascading waterfalls, before cruising across the Nadi Basin back to Denarau

fields.title: Private Cruises in the Most Beautiful Lagoons on the Planet
fields.description:
Wapaye and his crew offer tailor-made cruises.
Accommodating up to 8 people, you will cross the most beautiful lagoons on the planet.
From Huahine to Bora Bora via Raiatea and Tahaa, from Tahiti to Moorea or the Tuamotus.
You will taste the delicious local gastronomy.
Paddles, wake board, snorkeling and hiking will enhance your anchorages and stopovers.
Enjoy sumptuous sunrises and sunsets in a breathtaking setting.

fields.title: 4-Hour Private Freediving Photoshoot In Isla Mujeres
fields.description: I provide a unique photoshooting session on the caribean side of Isla Mujeres, where no boats are coming and no divers allowed to dive, wild reef and beautiful conditions
fields.supplier: Malek Bee Photography and Video Productions

fields.title: Private Airport Transfer Service

The Drakensberg region is extraordinary, thanks to the dramatically beautiful setting. This region is home to the awe-inspiring mountain range which is predominantly found in the KwaZulu Natal Province. There are unique activities such as Mountain hiking, game viewing and sight seeing the beautiful valleys and hills in the Midlands Meander area.

fields.title: Full-Day Private Safari Tour From Durban to Hluhluwe-Imfolozi Game Reserve
fields.description:
This tour departs from Durban at 6am and returns back to Durban at 6pm.

Hluhluwe–Imfolozi Park, formerly Hluhluwe–Umfolozi Game Reserve, is the oldest proclaimed nature reserve in Africa. It consists of 960 km² of hilly topography 280 kilometres north of Durban in central KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa and is known for its rich wildlife and conservation efforts.

Hluhluwe–Imfolozi Park is a beautiful game reserve. You will experience the African bush at its best. You will see the big 5 and many many more animals. You will see elephants, lions, giraffes, rhinoceros, leopards, cheetahs, kudus, and many many more. Also to be seen are many different birds, trees, the hills, and much more. You will be amazed at how beautiful this place really is.

fields.title: Full Day Private Tour - Isimangaliso Wetland Park - World Heritage Site
fields.description:
iSimangaliso Wetland Park, KwaZulu Natal South Africa is officially the first world heritage site in South Africa. This place of wonder is situated on the north coast of KwaZulu Natal and stretches from the small village of St Lucia in the South to the border of Mozambique in the North.

The area is enormous and offers incredible biodiversity. The South (St Lucia) offers a good base from where to explore as one may encounter Hippos wandering the streets at night in the residential area to the odd Leopard that frequents the area as well. St Lucia is truly a wildlife paradise with numerous species found both within and bordering the town. This is a tour never to be missed

fields.title: Castles and Cathedrals Tour of England

Here is your chance to follow your own Historian of the Middle Ages to some of the most important historic places in England. Grab the opportunity to see the past come alive - walk in the steps of Anne Boleyn - see the incomparable 1000-year-old Canterbury Cathedral - visit amazing Pubs!

fields.title: Secrets of the Berlin Wall - On and off the Beaten Path
fields.description:
We meet at Bornholmer Strasse, where the Fall of the Berlin Wall began and hear why my parents weren't the only ones who missed it. From there, we take the train to a former Ghost Station underneith the border and explore the Berlin Wall Memorial. Some of the best preserved remnants of the Wall can be found here and some of the most spectacular escape stories happened here as well. Where were the most famous escape tunnels? What happened to the buildings in the No Man's Land? And why was this the site of the first victims of the Wall?

Afterwards we head to a more remote area of the former border and learn how East and West developed along the Wall. How could someone build a treehouse in the Death Strip? Why are there still squats along the border? And what does a petting zoo have to do with the Wall? We'll even see a forgotten WW2 ruin, before finishing in an African-Jamaican beach bar, which opened in the former Death Strip - just around the corner from the East Side Gallery.

Upgrade your experience to enjoy a guided walk through the Kazimierz district, the Old Jewish Quarter in Kraków.

fields.title: Krakow: Jewish Ghetto Guided Tour
fields.description: During World War II, the Poguzhe district was the site of a Jewish ghetto, but even now, 75 years after the end of the war, the district keeps a part of those events. Much of it reminds its current inhabitants of the horrors of war and of the need to prevent such things from happening. You'll see the famous Plac Bohaterów Getta (Ghetto Heroes' Square), where Jews were selected and taken to concentration camps, also you'll see a fragment of the original Ghetto wall , which now serves as a monument and place of pilgrimage for many Jews. There are houses where thousands of displaced Jews used to live, and the pharmacy "Under the Eagle".It's always very interesting to walk these streets and learn their history from a to z

fields.title: Private ATV/ Quad Bike Safari in Riga, Latvia
fields.description: Quad bike safari is an excellent opportunity to enjoy some adrenaline-fueled time in Riga. fields.title: 2-Day Guided Overnight Hike & Buddhist Temple Stay in Shichimenzan
fields.description:
This is a rare opportunity to spend a night in a temple that is not set up for tourists. The temple is still operating as it did 700 years ago performing multiple daily ceremonies. Unlike typical tourist temples, you will have an opportunity to see everything on the inside and get to see how full time monks live in Japan. 

This is a temple only reachable by climbing the mountain, and there are many Japanese Buddhist practioners who climb this as a pilgrimage route, so this is a genuine experience.

captions: The view of Mt. Fuji from the temple is one of the best in Japan.
It takes 3 to 4 hours to reach the temple on well maintained trails.
Lanterns mark the way all the way up.
The temple gate perfectly frames Mt. Fuji.
The temple gate perfectly frames Mt. Fuji.
Keishin-in the temple we will spend the night.
Dinner is very simple and eaten together.
Typical Buddhist vegetarian meal, with some Sake' as a bonus.
Sleeping arrangements are minimal and communal in keeping with the pilgrimage history.
Kuonji temple in Minobu, the head temple of Nichiren Buddhism we visit after the hike.

fields.title: La Barca Cantina - All-Inclusive New Year's Fireworks Cruise
fields.description: Experience New Year's Eve in a whole new way - a cruise down the Hudson River, an all-you-can eat Mexican buffet, a Standard Open Bar, a DJ dance party and Fireworks at Midnight!

fields.description: Give yourself the pleasure of making a stop and live the experience of visiting a country with many tourist attractions, a cosmopolitan city, currently considered the city with the most skyscrapers in Latin America and at the same time surrounded by nature, we have the Panama Canal, one of the most important engineering works in the world.

captions: Plaza Herrera Old Town of Panama

fields.title: 7 Days Private Tour - Isimangaliso Wetlands Park and Drakensberg From Durban
fields.description:
The 7 day tour of the Isimangaliso Wetlands Park, Hlhluwe Imfolozi Game Reserve and the Drakensberg Mountain Region is the best of what one would come to Africa to see. 

You get to see so many animals in their natural habitat. The birds. The African bush full with trees, flowers and all. The longest mountain range in the Drakensberg Mountains. You'll see the ancient bushman paintings. You also experience a night under the African sky in a Camp Site. The 2 Hour Hippo and Croc Boat Cruise is a cherry on top.

fields.description: This is a private event tailored to your level of experience. You will be with only your group and no other participants on the newest and best equipment with extremely experienced guides. They are trained for your safety in Wilderness First Aid, Avalanche Certified, and have all the appropriate equipment to make your safety our primary concern.

fields.title: Live the gold: Sacred Lagoon of Guatavita and Muisca Indigenous Cabildo
fields.description:
If you are looking to walk in the footsteps of the Legend of El Dorado and live an enriching ecotourism experience, this plan is for you. We will have a wonderful walk through the Sacred Lagoon of Guatavita located at 3100 meters above sea level, with a local guide, who will teach us about the Legend of El Dorado, emblematic of our pre-Columbian culture.
We will also have the opportunity to meet the Indigenous council in muysc cubun (Muisca language, the path that crosses dreams), we will have the opportunity to reach the Cusmui (Muisca sacred house), to learn about the Muisca cosmogony and its interpretation of the world.

Low level
Time: approximately 9 hours
Cold weather
Altimetry 3100 masl

fields.title: Bioluminescent Private Night Tours From Montego Bay
fields.description:
This place itself is magical. This water contains lots of phosphorus minerals, so when disturbed it illuminates very brightly, the glow is cause by the small micro organisms that illuminates when touched. It is very amazing to see travelers in the water at night when it glows. If travelers choose to swim, once you get out of the water you will see your swimsuit and body light up as you move around.

The water is not very deep, only about 3 or 4 feet and life jackets are available for those who need them.

This is a private customizable trip which also gives you the choice to stop for food at your own expenses (Scotchies).

Each of our drivers has good knowledge of the routes they have idea of traffic jam hours and know how to take alternative routes to reach on time from your destination or a tourist place with safety. We are equipped with the best chauffeurs to provide you chauffeur service in Dubai. Our professional chauffeur service will be at your doorstep to serve you with safety and comfort ability.

fields.title: Full Day Bus Tour in Hiroshima and Miyajima
fields.description:
Join this full-day bus tour from Hiroshima Station, as we will visit some popular attractions. The first stop will be Itsukushima Shrine at Miyajima Island, which is famous for the historic site of Shinto. This shrine is known as one of the most scenic spots in Japan. 

You will definitely enjoy the beautiful red shrine as if it were floating in the middle of the sea. We will also visit the Atomic Bomb Dome, which tells us how miserable the destructive effects of nuclear warfare are and how important peace is. We will also visit Hiroshima Peace Memorial Park and Museum.

fields.title: Hiroshima and Miyajima 1 Day Bus Tour from Osaka and Kyoto
fields.description:

fields.description:
• Our Ephesus Tour prices are more reasonable than cruise shore excursions.

• We guarantee you will complete the tour and back to ship ( Ephesus / Kusadasi Port ) on time.

fields.title: Private Exploration of The Snæfellsnes Peninsula
fields.description:
The peninsula of Snæfellsnes is usually called "Iceland in miniature". It is a small piece of land in the western part of Iceland, and still offers all the different types of landscapes one can find in Iceland: Waterfalls, volcanic craters, glacier, lava fields, lakes, and more ...

On this tour, your guide will show you all the highlights of the peninsula. An amazing journey through volcanic history and Icelandic sagas.

fields.title: Donut or Sofa Boat Ride Watersport Tour Package in Dubai
fields.description:
Many families enjoy all the water sports towable on Dubai trip or who have a residence here. Donut ride in Dubai is also an adventurous water sport activity. Inflatable shaped as donut pulled with a speedboat in Dubai waters. Multiple people can sit on the donut and feel the water splash in an enthralling ride over the huge water boundary.

Sea Life Water Sports Dubai gets the expectational thrilling donut ride in Dubai for you and your loved ones to witness the panorama view of sunset and coastline. Our powerful speedboat and team of instructors will take care of your safety so that you can enjoy the ride to the fullest.

Thrilling Donut Ride in Dubai with Sea Life Water Sports
Donut Boat Ride Package in Dubai with Sea Life

fields.title: 8-Day Giza, Cairo, Luxor and Aswan Tour from Cairo
fields.description:
Enjoy a great journey in Egypt through Nile Cruise.
 First in Cairo to visit the Giza Pyramids and the Egyptian Museum then flying to Luxor to start your Nile cruise tour . See remarkable ruins and gorgeous panorama between Luxor and Aswan on a luxurious 5-day cruise before returning to Cairo to depart.

fields.title: Full-Day Tour Pyramids Sphinx passing by the Great Egyptian Museum
fields.description:
Visit Pyramids & Sphinx 
one of the seven wonders of the ancient world, the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chefren and Mykerinus and Sphinx then to the Valley Temple facing the great 
Visit The Grand Egyptian Museum 
The Great Egyptian Museum, GEM is an archaeological museum under construction in Giza, Egypt. When inaugurated, The GEM will be the largest archaeological museum in the world. It’ll house artifacts of ancient Egypt including the complete Tutankhamun collection, many pieces will be displayed for the first time.

fields.title: Palace of Versailles and Gardens by Bus from Paris
fields.description:
Start by meeting at a central point in Paris and transfer by bus to Versailles.
Enjoy a relaxing and comfortable transportation. Upon arrival, get a stess-free access to the palace at a shcedule time entrance. Then, discover the opulence, beauty, and history of the palace on a self-tour with an audioguide.

After your visit of the palace, take some free time to stroll around the beautiful French Gardens. After some time exploring the gardens by yourself, hop back on the bus for your journey back to central Paris.

fields.title: Explore Windsor Castle and Hampton Court Palace
fields.description:
Take this private driver tour to ensure you have your own historical expert with you in the surroundings of your own private vehicle. Find out all the tips to help you make the most of your time inside the castle and palace and how to skip the long entry lines that can sometimes happen at such famous sites. We will inform you of the rules of each venue to ensure a smooth and enjoyable visit for you. 

While you drive to the venues our guides will be able to discuss many facts and the history of the royal family in the United Kingdom to help make the drive seem short and entertaining. 

We will also book and arrange a wonderful traditional pub lunch for your group to enjoy after you visit Windsor Castle and before you enter Hampton Court Palace. 

This truly is a special day for any royal family fan and covers the two most famous royal buildings close to London. Take unbelievable photos and videos that you can look back on fondly. Also you never know who you might see at Windsor Castle!

fields.title: Full-Day Private Tour from Haifa to Old City of Acre
fields.description:
Our tour will start in an amazing lookout from Mt. Carmel, from there will tour the Bahai Gardens (if they are open), we will pass by the German Colony in Haifa and talk about the Temples guys who left there housed in Germany and arrived to Israel 180 years ago.

You can add an authentic culinary tour for lunch in one of the most local and interesting neighborhood - Wadi Nisnas, for extra payment. 

We will continue driving to the Old City of Acre (about 40 min driving), then we will meet the amazing preserved Crusaders underground city at the Knights Halls. We will tour between the alleys of the Turkish market and the Turkish Bath (not an active one) and will end in a secret ancient Templar tunnel which was discovered only on 1994.

fields.title: Private Car & Driver Multi-Day Round Tour in Sri Lanka
fields.description:
We offer you travel solutions and holiday packages which are made as per your very own requirements.
We offers Day tours, excursions, round tours, wildlife holidays, and cultural tours.

fields.title: Skydiving Tandem Experience
fields.description:
Sky, clouds, wind, speed and infinite freedom – this is what skydiving is all about.

Our professional team are people who are passionate about the sky and freedom. We are united by common interest towards positive emotions, unlimited adventure and infinite joy – everything that skydiving can offer you. Our main goals are to simply enjoy life and share this unique opportunity of skydiving with others.

Tandem jumps are organized by professional Skydive instructors with more than 10 years of international experience and USPA ratings. We do it at from 4000m height with the best view in Baltics.

fields.title: 3 Days Tour in Uganda Gorilla Private Safari
fields.description: Have a tailor made safari just for you when you book this three days Uganda gorilla trekking safari. You will enjoy gorilla watching in their natural habitat, hiking and photographing will be the game of the trip. We shall have communities visit on third day of the trip to experience the Batwa culture. The guide-Driver and the team will take care of all logistics so you will just enjoy the experience and relax into your safari, spot the gorillas observe their behaviors and learn all about them from your guide. This is one of the life time safari experience.

fields.title: A Nature Walk on the Wing: Alaskan Birds and Wildlife Eco-Tour
fields.description:
We will experience our local birds, the ecosystem that supports them, and of course the keystone megafauna mammal species with whom they share their space. This tour is special because we focus on bird families and highlight how the patterns of migrations and flux in the environment/seasonal changes interplay with one another. A visit to the AWCC and our favorite local spots guarantees an up close viewing of Alaskan wildlife.

Depending on the season, we may observe: 

raptors (eagles, falcons, owls, hawks, etc.)
mammals (moose, bears, lynx, hares, belugas...)
coastal birds
migratory birds....and many more!

Whether you are an experienced birder, new to birding, or you simply love our feathered friends, this tour is a great way to learn more and experience our favorite local bird species. This is more than a birding tour - it is a holistic look at how the local ecosystems vary and interact to support the thousands of bird species that live here both year-round and on a migratory basis.

fields.title: Full Day Tour from Arusha
fields.description:
This is a typical itinerary for a full day tour in Arusha town where you will learn about Arabica coffee, Interact with the locals and have local lunch, explore waterfalls and canoe in lake duluti. We will pick you up from your hotel in Arusha town and drive to Tengeru town. From here you will meet our local guides and brief you about the tour then you can choose between Cycling or walking,
Then you will start cycling/hiking through the village, this is the chance to interact with local people in the, where you will share greetings and have some pictures while heading into the coffee plantations to learn and to make your own cup of coffee using traditional ways. After coffee we will have a 30mins hike to waterfalls and back.
Then after we will board our bicycle/car and ride to tengeru town for a hot local lunch and the after we go for canoe at Lake Duluti and learn different species of birds and about the legendary of the lake in connection to the mere tribe’s, rituals

fields.title: Motocross off-road experience
fields.description:
With us you can expect an experience that you will never forget.
We have perfect conditions for motocross under palm trees 365 days a year.
It doesn't matter if you've never ridden a motorcycle or if you're a pro.
We have the largest and newest range of vehicles in Tenerife to choose the one that's right for you. From a high-end electric bike to a 350cc motocross bike.
Safety is our top priority. Our protective clothing and our motorcycles are of the highest standard.

Our owner and trainer Fabian is internationally known and will be happy to answer any questions you may have.

We look forward to spending an unforgettable experience with you.

fields.title: Private Half-Day Tour to the Cultural Historic Sites of Marrakech
fields.description: This tour gives you a unique insight into Marrakech, unveiling the city's little-known history and mysteries. Explore the heart of the old city, starting with the famous Koutoubia mosque, to follow our guide to the Bahia Palace, then the Mellah district, before strolling through the colorful souks of Marrakech.

fields.title: La Perle by Dragone Platinum Or VIP Tickets VIP With Dinner
fields.description: La Perle features a breathtaking fusion of immersive artistic performances, imagery and technology. La Perle is influenced by Dubai’s rich culture, vibrant present and aspirational future, which is brought to life by awe-inspiring stunts and special effects that will leave viewers speechless. A must-not miss show that travels you to realms of an entire different world with its miraculous performances is mastered by the world renowned director, Franco Dragon. you will be amazed to see the on-stage pool (aqua stage) that uses 2.7 million litres water innovatively in acts and has 1300 seats occupied by the audience in a circular orientation; the round arrangement is done to keep the audience intimate to the live performances from all possible ends.

fields.title: Private, Small and Big Groups Rent a Van in Dubai
fields.description:

fields.title: Private Guided Kentucky Bourbon and Whiskey Tour
fields.description:
There's a big different between hiring a transportation company offering a ride to distilleries, and hiring a private tour guide, planner and driver that ensures guests learn and see as much as they possibly want to about Kentucky Bourbon Whiskey. 
Most companies selling "Bourbon Tours" are selling a ride to and from distilleries, where the tours occur. That's enough for many visitors, but there's so much more to see, learn and taste.
My guests learn all about Bourbon and Kentucky before we ever set foot in a distillery. My tour happens along the way.
You'll be escorted by someone who knows each and every site we visit; someone who knows the best routes and scenic back roads; and have that many distillery workers can't discuss.
Small groups are preferred so that we can have a relaxed conversation about distilling in Kentucky, rather than teacher-student interaction. But I sometimes accept larger groups who want to learn and see more than a typical "tour" offers.

This tropical rain forest is a magical setting for a spectacular zipline adventure.

Enroute to the Zip, you will soar up overland with magnificent view of Mt Evans Range, the rustic outskirts of the farmlands, and the lower Sabeto estuaries. The great thing about this package is the fact that the departure time is very flexible and we work with you to customize your day.

We will pick you up from the hotel at about 11:00 am. The boat starts from the most beautiful place in Hurghada – New Marina Port. During the first stop at coral reefs, the boat will go down to a depth of two metres underwater, and through the glass windows you will be able to see a wide range of fish and corals. A 30-minute snorkeling near Giftun Island will let you on your own explore and appreciate the beauty and uniqueness of the the Red Sea world, after which you will have lunch and soft drinks on the boat.

Nestled in the cool shadows of the big man himself, the Garden of the Sleeping Giant is one of the more pleasant discoveries you’ll make during your visit to Fiji. The flight will then venture up into the mighty Mt.Evans Range to explore the Sleeping Giant. Marko, the founder and manager of Studio tipoRenesansa, the only relief printmaking studio in Slovenia, has more than 20 years of experience in teaching calligraphy, letter carving in stone, and design & print workshops. fields.title: Private adventure: Christmas in a Castle
fields.description:
Your magical adventure will start from your hotel. You will stay warm and cosy while we will drive you through medieval villages and enchanting countryside. 
At the first point you will explore a village market while your fingers will be snuggly wrapped around some turmeric latte or mulled wine. 
Under a dove grey sky the colours of the castle Christmas market will make the world brighter than ever. 
Later on you will explore christmas lights of the Leeds castle.You will stay at the cobblestone where the horses passed over to carry the goods into the citadel within. 
In the medieval times of uncertainty, when armies were conquering cities, a castle was always a safe place, a house, a fortress. It was a place to protect your loved ones.
When winter’s moon hangs in the sky you will come back to your hotel ready to make this Christmas special.

See and get the best pictures of the art murals painted by the locals who had a very dark past, but now they have changed their lives through the art. At the end, we get to the top of the barrio to get a general view of Lima.

We run this tour along with "Color Energía '', an organization created by local artists and neighbours of Leticia,, which is a "barrio" located on the hillsides. We support each other in this activity to promote this project as a tourist attraction. fields.title: Cerro Manquehue Traverse Private Tour with Pickup and Lunch
fields.description:
After agreeing on a meeting time we will pick you up and drive you to the start of the trail: The foot of Cerro Carbon.
From here we need to climb around 600 meters to the summit of this mountain top. We will enjoy spectacular views over the whole city and take a small break.
Here we start walking towards the biggest mountain of this range: Cerro Manquehue. Both mountains are connected by a spectacular ridge.
Here we often see local wildlife including Andean Condors and foxes.

After 200 meters more climbing we will arrive on the summit of Manquehue where we eat traditional Chilean empanadas.
From the summit you can see the Central Andean mountains including Cerro El Plomo, El Altar and La Paloma Glacier.
We can choose to climb another peak in the range: Manquehito; or start descending towards Cerro Carbon again.
After a long and rewarding hike we arrive back at our car from where we bring you back to your requested drop off point.

captions: View of Cerro Manquehue from the path inbetween Carbon and Manquehue
On the way to the summit of Carbon
Rocky part to start the last climb up Manquehue

fields.title: 3-Days Private Tour Sierra de Ramon Trekking
fields.description:
On our first day we hike from the road to Farellones ( 1000 masl ) all the way up to Cerro Provincia ( 2500 masl ). On our way we enjoy spectacular views of the Central Chilean mountain range and see amazing fauna and flora, including Andean Condor and sometimes even Wild Andean Cats ( no Puma ).

We sleep in a refugio or tent on top of this mountain and cook a nice dinner.

The following day we traverse to Cerro Ramon, with 3200 masl the highest mountain of the range. This remote part of the hike is known for its dramatic viewpoints. We will help you spot some epic mountains in the area, including Tupungato, Marmolejo and San José Vulcano.

Again, we sleep in a refugio or tent on top of the mountain.
At night we enjoy views over Santiago while searching for stars.

The next day our descent starts towards the Cajon del Maipo, where after descending almost 2500 meters we arrive in the town of El Manzano. From here our pick up brings us back to our hotel.

captions: View of Cerro El Plomo, Tupungato and more more from the summit of Cerro Provincia
Cactus on the lower parts of the hike.

fields.description:
Explore France’s so-called Red City with the help of a local guide on this private walking excursion through Albi. You’ll learn about its medieval history while marveling at architectural feats such as the Berbie Palace and Sainte-Cécile Cathedral. 

Start your tour at the Place Sainte-Cécile, and learn about the history of the breathtaking Cathedral of Sainte-Cécile, around which the whole town was constructed in medieval times. 

Then, discover the Palais de la Berbie (Berbie Palace), one of the oldest castles in France. With a history dating back to the 13th century, the palatial complex tells a rich history of Albi’s royal past, and is now the site of the Toulouse-Lautrec museum.

From the vantage point of Albi’s famous Pont Vieux (Old Bridge), you’ll have an unbeatable panorama of one of the most beautiful towns in Southern France, and unobstructed views of the surrounding River Tarn.

fields.title: Visit Alcazaba and Roman Theater (Entrance included)
fields.description:
When you visit a city you appreciate that they help you and guide you, that's why our goal is for you to feel like one more person from Malaga and show you all its corners.
Do not go crazy looking for information about the city because we will show it to you as if we had known each other all our lives!!!

fields.title: Private Transfer from Florence to Pisa with 2 hours for sightseeing
fields.description: With our private transfer service, you can enjoy optimizing your travel time and the comfort of our cars. Our experienced local driver always has your safety and comfort in mind. From the beginning of the trip, when he picks you up in Florence at your desired time and takes care of your luggage, until the end of your journey in your chosen location in Pisa. Here begins your private stress-free trip full of wonderful authentic experiences and insights into the local culture. Our travel experts have chosen the most interesting sightseeing stops and top-rated attractions for you to choose from and enrich your journey. You will travel comfortably with a reliable driver who speaks English and has a good knowledge of the area. The only thing you need to do is relax while being taken care of. Other routes with sightseeing stops across Europe are available on our website.

fields.title: Bateaux New York Christmas Day Premier Dinner Cruise
fields.description: Celebrate the magic of the season on a luxurious Christmas Day Premier Plus Dinner Cruise aboard New York’s glass-enclosed Bateaux – Manhattan’s most premium experience on the water. You and your guests will enjoy a holiday 3-course, plated dinner freshly prepared by our chef, full bar service, and City Cruises’ distinctive hospitality. While onboard, experience exceptional views of New York City’s iconic skyline from an incredibly unique perspective, a live pianist, and festive décor. Our team will happily take care of the details, leaving you to celebrate the holidays on the Hudson and East Rivers with your friends and family. Happy Holidays!

fields.title: Koshary Food Experience Private Tour
fields.description: Finding a new way to appreciate food is one of the best ways to discover a foreign culture in your chosen destination. Koshary food tour. The Koshary as we call it in Egypt, is an all-time favourite street food. In most parts of the Middle East you cant find that food, only in Egypt. Koshary is made out of rice, pasta in all its forms, lentils, onions, noodles, sauce and chickpeas, which constitute a meal that suits everyone with its special taste.

fields.title: Pigeon's Food Experience Private Tour
fields.description:
Finding a new way to appreciate food is one of the best ways to discover a foreign culture in your chosen destination. Pigeon's food tour. 

Pigeon's food, it's famous traditional food in Egypt and the middle east. It's a tasty meal, served for lunch or dinner.
Pigeons are widely eaten in many countries, including Britain and Ireland. 

Pigeon Meat Good for Health? Pigeon or squab are considered a great delicacy in some parts of the world, and they are widely used as game bird meat. Pigeon is considered to be an excellent source of protein, iron, phosphorus, and vitamin B12.

fields.title: Full Day London Tour Includes Entry passes
fields.description:
London, the capital of England and the United Kingdom, is a 21st-century city with history stretching back to Roman times. At its centre stand the imposing Houses of Parliament, the iconic ‘Big Ben’ clock tower and Westminster Abbey, site of British monarch coronations. Across the Thames River, the London Eye observation wheel provides panoramic views of the South Bank cultural complex, and the entire city.
Spend a full day exploring London with your personal chauffeur and car. From pickup to drop-off, you'll have the services of the car and driver at your service and can go wherever you like. No messing with taxis or the Tube; this tour option is great for families with children or elderly travelers with mobility challenges. Private vehicle for your party only. Make your own itinerary. Spend the full day exploring at your own pace Great for independent travelers. Included with this tour is a One Day London Pass which allows you to visit over 80 sites in London

fields.title: Best of Naples and Pompeii Private Full-Day Tour with Luxury Car - WOW Tour
fields.description:
Only 1 day in Naples? There is still time to visit many of the city’s most iconic attractions and the best-preserved ancient Roman city. 
The itinerary focuses on the best of Naples: Spaccanapoli, Santa Chiara, Gesù Nuovo, the veiled Christ, Piazza del Plebiscito, Galleria Umberto I, Teatro San Carlo, Caste Nuovo. Via Partenope and castel dell’Ovo. 
After a delicious pizza, you will reach Pompeii to visit the vastest and best-preserved archaeological site in the entire world. 

We will take care of everything: tickets, pick up, drop off, all transfers, experienced and friendly guide.
Everything is included, even lunch, for a hassle-free experience.

It is an Exclusive Private Tour only for your group!

Cappella San Severo: Your knowledgeable guide will propose alternatives on Tuesday (closing day) and when tickets are unavailable.

fields.title: Private Pastry Class with Catherine Near Arc de Triomphe
fields.description:
Enjoy this unique pastry class with Catherine in her private Parisian appartment.
She is a cookbook writer specialized in French cuisine and French pastries.
Catherine has travelled all around the globe and speaks fluent English.
This class offers you the experience of a personnalised activity with a real Parisian, very close to the Arch of Triumph.

fields.title: Marangu 5 Days
fields.description: One of the more interesting aspects of Marangu Route is that it is the only route up Mount Kilimanjaro that doesn't allow camping, so instead of sleeping in tents, trekkers stay in permanent huts instead. While staying at those huts, trekkers will sleep in bunk beds equipped with a simple mattress and pillow.

fields.title: Explore an Amusement Arcade and Pop culture at Night Tour in Kyoto
fields.description:
I'll take you on a private night tour to a modern amusement arcade in Kyoto. This will be a really fun and exciting time in Kyoto with me, a guide to Japanese pop culture. You may experience traditional and historical culture throughout the day at shrines and temples. Then, join this night trip to explore Japanese pop culture by playing cutting-edge arcade games. Send a message if you would want to modify the start time. By 10 p.m., children are permitted to enter amusement arcades with their parents.

First, I'll offer a brief talk on Japanese amusement arcades and related pop culture. Following that, we have fun playing the arcade games below. In some arcade games the settings screen is only displayed in Japanese and I can help you to set them. 100-400JPY each play is the price.

- Claw machines/Crane games/UFO catchers
- Car racing games like Mario Kart
- Dancing games with cutting-edge motion capture system
- Unique and various token games originating in Japan

fields.title: 5-Day Nile Cruise Tour from Luxor To Aswan
fields.description: Cruise the Nile River for 4 nights aboard the 5 stars Nile Cruise! Explore the archaeological icons of ancient Egypt with your own private and expert local guides. Gain exclusive access to the tomb of “the boy king", Tutankhamun, in the Valley of the Kings, sail the Nile in a felucca, and view Aswan’s treasures.

fields.title: Tour to the West Bank in Luxor
fields.description: Representative will Pick you up from Your Hotel in Luxor to Enjoy Half-day Tour to visit the west bank of Luxor ,The ancient Egyptian sites of Luxor’s West Bank are so spread out that a tour is your only option. Beat the crowds with your own private guide and check off the highlights in just half a day: the Valley of the Kings, the Temple of Hatshepsut, and the Colossi of Memnon, complete with temple excavations.

fields.title: Nile Cruise Private Tour Luxor to Aswan 5 Days 4 Nights
fields.description: A Nile River cruise is one of the best ways to see the ruins of ancient Egypt. This cruise travels between Luxor and Aswan for five days and takes you into the heart of Egypt with daily excursions to major landmarks. Select the option to choose your private guide.

fields.title: Private Full-Day Luxor Highlights East and West Banks
fields.description: Make the most of your time in Luxor with this private tour that ensures you see all the highlights of both the East and West Bank. In the company of just your party and an Egyptologist guide, explore such ancient sites as the Temple of Karnak, the Valley of Kings, and the Temple of Ramses III.

fields.title: Leeds Castle Private Tour From London With Admission Tickets
fields.description:
Visit Leeds Castle, the 12th-century Leeds Castle is among Europe’s best-preserved medieval landmarks, with more than nine centuries of history represented in the building and grounds. Sprawled over 500 acres (202 hectares) and surrounded by a regal moat, the stone castle and its gardens offer a peek into the past as well as a variety of present-day, quintessentially English events and activities with this independent day trip which includes an entrance ticket with round-trip private vehicle service from your London accommodation at a time that suits you.

 • Self-guided tour of Leeds Castle including private hotel pickup and drop-off 
 • Designed for travelers wanting to combine convenience with flexibility 
 • Bypass lines often in excess of one hour with a skip-the-line ticket 
 • Explore the regal residence at your own pace.

fields.title: Day Tour To Luxor From Marsa Alam
fields.description: At 4:00 am our representative will pick you up from your Hotel in Marsa Alam. You will be transferred by private A/C vehicle to the West Bank where you will visit the Valley Of The Kings, the magnificence of the grandeur of architecture which was used for burial, there are many kings buried in this valley. Followed by a visit to the Temple of Queen Hatshepsut that known as El Dir El Bahari which was built by Queen Hatshepsut the daughter of Thutmosis I, who ruled Egypt about 20 years during the 18th Dynasty (approximately 1490-1469 B.C). Continue your day Tour to The Colossi of Memnon which is remains of the mortuary temple of Amenhotep III. Lunch Break at Local Restaurants based on full meal for each person but beverages are not included. Then transfer to the East Bank and visit in Luxor to continue your day tour. Visit the Karnak Temple, the greatest example of worship in the history, dedicated to the God Amun, his wife Mut and their son Khonsu.

fields.title: Tour to Dendera and Abydos Temples
fields.description: Get ready to discover the ancient sites. First, visit Abydos, the ancient Egyptian believed of god (Lord of the underworld) to be buried there. The temple was built by King Seti I and completed by King Ramsess II, known as the temple of Seti I. It is located in Abydos city about 420 km to the south of Cairo in the Sohag Government, and 135 km from Luxor. The paintings of the Gods and Pharaohs on the walls of the Osiris Temple at Abydos are among the most beautifully preserved in Egypt. Then continue to Dendera to visit the Temple of Hathor, goddess of love and joy. The temple is located in Dendera which is situated north of Luxor.

fields.title: Full Day Small Group Tour in Cambodia's 4 Major Temples
fields.description: The UNESCO-listed temple of Angkor Wat is Cambodia’s most visited attraction and it’s even more magnificent beneath the glow of the rising sun. On this small-group tour, rise early to watch the sunrise over Angkor Wat, then benefit from the cooler weather and fewer crowds of the morning to explore the surrounding temples. Then, visit Angkor Thom, admire the Gate to Bayon, discover Bayon Temple,and we going to have break time for breakfast somewhere around the temple area and see the Buddhist temple of Taprom (tomb raider ) a big root of the jungle growing up and stop the last at Banteay kdie teampl, before return hotel ,

fields.description: This unique combo allows travelers to do two "must do" tours that is highly recommended by other travelers. The fusion of Bamboo Rafting down the river, coupled with the Luminous Lagoon is a perfect evening of relaxation and experiencing a unique phenomenon.

fields.title: Gelsenkirchen Private Walking Tour with Professional Guide
fields.description:
Gelsenkirchen's history starts in 1150, but it remained a tiny village until the 19th century when the Industrial Revolution led to the growth of the entire area. In the early 20th century, Gelsenkirchen was called the "city of a thousand fires" for the flames of mine gasses flaring at night time. On this tour, you will visit one of the most important Renaissance castles of the North West region. Admire the Consol theatre, a theatre located on a former coal mine. See the Music Theater, planned, designed, and built by the Englishman Robert Adams, the two Germans Norbert Kricke and Paul Dierkes, the Swiss Jean Tinguely, and the French Yves Klein. Visit the artist's village Halfmanshof, a residential and working artistic community in 1931, which became a hub for famous artists in the 60s and 70s.

All attraction entrances are to be paid on the spot by travelers since attractions are not mandatory. This tour does not include any attractions with require paid entrances.

fields.title: Halle Private Walking Tour with a Professional Guide
fields.description:
Halle, the hometown of the composer Georg Friedrich Handel, is a town situated on the Saale River with a population of about 230 000 inhabitants. As you stroll through the streets of this magnificent town, you will see the Market Square, a lively place that offers a lot of sights, from the red castle in the square to the monument of Georg Friedrich Handel. Learn all about the Church of Our Lady, a late Gothic church famous for several facts: the resting place of Martin Luther's death mask, for being the place of Handels baptism, and for Bach's consecrated church organ. See the facade of the Handel House, a museum dedicated to the life of the musician Georg Friedrich Handel and to the musical history of the region. Discover the highlights of Halle, and learn more about the famous musician Handel.

All attraction entrances are to be paid for on the spot by travelers since attractions are not mandatory. This tour does not include any attractions with require paid entrances.

fields.title: Harburg Private Guided Walking Tour
fields.description:
Strategically located above the Wörnitz River, Harburg is known for its medieval castle. It is a popular stop on a scenic route known as the Romantic Road, and it is worth a special trip. Discover the historic stone bridge, which was partially destroyed in 1945. Admire the Plant pillars at the market square, representing the greening and the hand artistic elements. Stroll around the city under the guidance of the local guide through the narrow streets of the old town and explore the beautiful Marktplatz Fountain.

All attraction entrances are to be paid for on the spot by travelers since attractions are not mandatory. This tour does not include any attractions with require paid entrances

fields.title: Lausanne Private Walking Tour with a Professional Guide
fields.description:
This city is a mixture of ancient and modern, as well as a very cosmopolitan example of the Swiss lifestyle. It rises in terraces on three hills above the north shore of Lake Geneva (Lac Léman). Lausanne is a city of sports, being the headquarters of the Olympic Committee and of the Court of Arbitration for Sport, having also the Swiss Film Archive as well. The city is officially titled the “Olympic Capital”. Pass the Musee des Beaux-Arts (Fine Art Museum), also known as the Palais de Rumine. It houses a modest but impressive art collection. Walk the Escalier du Marché, leading to the terrace of the cathedral. Visit the Rue du Bourg, once one of the main roads of old Lausanne. Wander through the Flon Quarter, the city’s ultra-contemporary zone. Journey through this fantastic hilly city of the Savoy Alps.

All attraction entrances are to be paid for on the spot by travelers since attractions are not mandatory. This tour does not include any attractions with require paid entrances.

fields.title: Half-Day Guided Tour by Speedboat of the Kotor Bay
fields.description:
A unique perspective into the natural landscape of the kotor fjord, combined with its amazing architecture, and history, gain a full insight into what made kotor the town it is today and see all the beauty of the Jewel of the Adriatic Sea.
As the tour starts you will enjoy a ride to the Lady of the rocks this artificial island is a majestic sight to behold and you will get 25 minutes to tour the church museum.
Following this, the ride continues all the way outside the bay and the next stop is the beautiful blue grotto or the blue cave where you can enjoy a swim!
The water here has a unique turquoise color and after 30 minutes of relaxing here, the trip continues with a panoramic drive around Mamula the prison island.
Coming back into the bay next stop is the submarine tunnels, entering one of the tunnels a short break of 10 minutes to enjoy a place where many famous movies were filmed.
And many more panoramic sights await on the way back to Kotor, providing insight into the whole bay.

fields.title: Private Tour, Beaches, Windmills, Monasteries in Patmos Island
fields.description: Meet your private driver at Skala port, to start a wonderful shore excursion to the most popular scene sites. More specifically in the “Holy Cave of the Apocalypse”, we will visit the windmills of Chora, for memorable photos, which date back to 1588

fields.title: Excursion on foot of Capo Miseno
fields.description: Guided walking tour on the coast of Miseno. A trekking experience immersed in nature. Capo Miseno is the extreme tip of the Phlegraean peninsula, in the immediate vicinity of the port of Miseno, in the municipality of Bacoli.

fields.title: Saint-Émilion : Private Walking Tour & Magnificent Views
fields.description:
This guided walk will allow you to learn more about the history of the development of the city, from its origins to the present day. Walk along the ramparts, imagine the life of the monks through the old monasteries and the magnificent views of the city.

An outside explanation of the monolithic church, the collegiate church, the palace of the archbishops, and the remains of the fortifications will be possible with the tour guide.

The advantage of booking a private walking tour is that the visit takes place at your own pace. This tour offers a high degree of flexibility whether you are looking for a tour that takes in all the famous sites or something more off the beaten track. Your private guide will have the knowledge and expertise to create the perfect walking tour, according to your wishes!

fields.title: Discover Real Saigon by Bike Half-Day Tour with Lunch
fields.description: This 5 hour bicycle tour will show you the REAL Saigon – Ho Chi Minh City that casual visitors rarely see. By bike, we will explore urban area narrow alleyways, markets, and backstreets as well as the charming local areas of Chinatown. End the tour with a buffet noodle style lunch in the local market.

fields.title: Paris: Priority-Access Eiffel Tower Tour by Elevator
fields.description: Marvel at the beauty of the "ville lumière" from the top of the symbol of Paris: the Eiffel Tower. You can let your knowledgeable tour guide escort you throughout a tour enabling the discovery of the French capital from above.

fields.title: Shore Excursion Patmos Monastery, Cave, Chora & Beach Private Driving Tour
fields.description:
Meet your private driver at Skala port, to start a wonderful shore excursion to the most popular scene sites. More specifically in the “Holy Cave of the Apocalypse”,  we will visit the windmills of Chora, for memorable photos, which date back to 1588
You continue your drive around the island to see its landscape of outstanding natural beauty comprised mostly of rocky hills, dozens of tongues of land reaching out into the sea, tranquil beaches, and many picturesque inlets. Passing by Grikos bay you will enjoy the virgin natural scene with crystal water before reaching at Bay of Lambi where the beach with its colorful stones gives a small souvenir to take home with us! Also, we will visit the "paralia Kampos" one of the most beautiful beaches in Patmos!

fields.description:
Book your Private Arrival Transfer from Genoa airport (GOA) to Savona Cruise Port.

fields.title: Normandy: Mont-Saint-Michel Private Walking Tour
fields.description:
Discover the history of Mont-Saint-Michel, from the Hundred Years' War to the French Revolution, on a fascinating walking adventure. Join your private guide to discover the area and take in the stunning Romanesque architecture perched on top of the cliffs contrasting with the surrounding marshland.

Arrive in Normandy and meet your guide outside the castle for a trip back in time as you walk around this outstanding site, dating back to the medieval era. Make the most of your guide's knowledge and expertise to customize your experience to your specific needs.

Explore the many wonders of this UNESCO World Heritage Site, with the option to visit the historic abbey, which served both as a pilgrimage site and a prison back in the day.

fields.title: Fribourg Scavenger Hunt and City Highlights Self Guided Tour
fields.description:
Discover Fribourg from a different perspective on a self-guided walking tour and scavenger hunt of the city. Solve riddles and clues that lead to the next location, showing all the city highlights.

- Solve interesting puzzles, have fun and learn new things about Fribourg
- Explore the city and find hidden gems at your own pace
- Try a new type of experience with your smartphone, the perfect mix between a walking tour, sightseeing, and a scavenger hunt.
- Enjoy the tour in English, French, German

fields.title: Olive Harvesting in Eastern Mani
fields.description:
Experience local Winter life in Mani, by partaking in the harvesting of olives. Under the experienced guidance of the field's owner, participate alongside a local crew in the methodical picking of olives, while viewing all the tasks that must be done to successfully harvest this crop. 
At the end, visit a local olive press to see how olives are turned into oil. Take a souvenir bottle home with you.

fields.title: Paris: Priority-Access Eiffel Tower Tour by Elevator
fields.description:
After meeting with your tour guide, enjoy priority access to the second floor of the Eiffel Tower to enjoy the views out over the "ville lumière". During your ascent, your tour guide will delight you with stories and facts about this mighty construction, which is known to be the symbol of the city of Paris. You will get to know all about the building itself and about the civil engineer who created it, Gustave Eiffel.

Your tour guide will also take the time to indicate to you all of the landmarks of Paris, including the Louvre Museum, the Notre-Dame Cathedral, Montmartre, and the Sacré-Cœur (just to mention a few). The view over the city of love is sure to take your breath away.

fields.title: Chenonceau Castle: Private Guided Walking Tour
fields.description:
Enjoy a walking tour of Chenonceau Castle with a local guide who will tailor the excursion to your tastes and introduce you to the castle’s beautiful places. Start at the entrance of the castle and then head to the charming gardens full of flowers.

Chenonceau castle has been classified a “Historic Monument” by the French Ministry of Culture and has been home to famous queens as Diane de Poitiers and Catherine de Medicis. Discover its original design and architecture and immerse yourself in the medieval period during this informative tour.

fields.title: Sea Kayak Day trip SW Paxos - Mongonissi to Avlaki
fields.description: During this sea kayaking tour we will visit Kaltsonissi Passage, Mongonissi blue Caves, Tripitos Arch, Ahandakas Cave, Mousmouli bay with a lot of caves and secret beaches, Galazio beach and Nerandou. We will end out tour in Avlaki beach. We will make several stops for swimming, snorkeling, having a rest or eating a snack.

fields.title: Languedoc-Roussillon: Pont du Gard Private Tour & History
fields.description:
Come and discover the highest Roman bridge-aqueduct in the world and its history with a licensed tour guide during a 1h30 private tour and admire its architecture, rare for its time and the best preserved now.

Built by the Romans around 50 AD, the Pont du Gard is the major element and most prestigious vestige of the ancient aqueduct of Nîmes, designed to bring water from the Eure spring, at the foot of the town of Uzès, to Nîmes.
It was declared a World Heritage Site by UNESCO in 1985.

You will also have time after the guided tour, to visit the museum by yourself (valid only during the opening hours of the museum).

fields.title: Salem Kids Walking History Tour
fields.description: Salem’s “must do” for visiting families, Salem kids tours have captivated and inspired guests for over ten years. Led by local educators who have a passion for history and a love for sharing stories with kids, Salem dids tours will inspire young learners, spark imagination, and invite kids to extend and share their knowledge after the tour is over. Our guides are committed to opening young minds and hearts to the fascinating history that surrounds us. Parents looking for a high-quality outdoor experience that the kids will love, enjoy, and remember choose Salem kids tours when planning family travel. Come on the tour that parents have described as “the best thing we did in Salem”.

Moc Chau and Son La are two places with great potential and advantages for tourism development. with a large natural area and abundant tourism resources, lush green tea hills, landscapes, a system of historical relics, diverse cultural heritage and the largest hydroelectric dam in Southeast Asia . Bach Long glass bridge in Moc Chau district, Son La province, is recognized as the world’s longest cliff-side path by Guinness World Records and the world's longest glass-bottomed bridge by the World Record Association and the EU’s Official World Record.

fields.description: This scenic flight takes you over the breathtakingly beautiful islets and reefs that dot the tropical landscape to the north of Efate. Lopevi Island is the closest active volcano to Vanuatu’s capital, Port Vila. Lopevi Volcano is one of the most scenically spectacular islands in the archipelago. As an almost perfect conical shaped volcanic island, it casts an impressive and commanding presence, jutting clear out of the water to a height of almost 5,000 feet. Lopevi Volcano forms the tallest peak in central Vanuatu. Lopevi’s explosive activity has increased in recent times with lava flows sometimes reaching the ocean. Evidence of old eruptions can be seen as scars cutting through Lopevi’s emerald forested slopes.

The Selous Game Reserve is a protected area in southern Tanzania. It covers a total area of 50,000 km² and has additional buffer zones. It was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1982 due to its wildlife diversity and undisturbed nature.

Large numbers of elephants, black rhinoceroses, cheetahs, giraffes, hippopotamuses and crocodiles live in this immense sanctuary, which measures 50,000 km2 and is relatively undisturbed by human impact. The park has a variety of vegetation zones, ranging from dense thickets to open wooded grasslands.

fields.title: In Water Oyster Farm Tour and Dining, Sydney
fields.description:
The in water oyster farm tour will take participants on a boat ride out to Sheridan's family's oyster farm with our farmers. Learn about the evolution of farming and see the current cultivation methods to grow our Sydney rock and Pacific oysters. Following the boat tour of our oyster farm, guests will then put on a waterproof suits we have provided and disembark with our farmers to their own in water table. You will then enjoy a fresh seafood platter where you will learn to open 18 oysters per person with fresh prawns and refreshments.

We welcome BYO if you have a bottle of something special you would like to drink.

fields.title: Discover Scuba Diving in a marine protected area
fields.description: Discover Scuba Diving in Tenerife s most varied marine ecosystem. This marine protected area is by far the best location for first time divers. Find out how easy it is to breath under the water and experience the sensation of weightlessness. Enjoy a 40min dive to a depth of no more than 6 meters surrounding Atlantic Oceans breath taking underwater life. Try diving with a personal Instructor, max 2 participants a dive. Free Photos, online registration PADI No previous experience required.

fields.title: Boracay Snorkeling & Island Hopping tour
fields.description: On this day, we will pick you from where you're staying in Boracay and you will be transferred to where we gonna take the traditional Banka boat. The key highlights of this experience is to explore the Boracay's best snorkeling spots and the best island beaches. We will visit the famous beach paradise, Puka shell beach to stroll on the beach, swim in the blue waters or just relax with on the beach. Coconut palm–lined beach with coral & shell sand, snorkeling, sunbathing & a nearby restaurant. This Coconut palm–lined beach with coral and shell sand is an ideal natural getaway for snorkeling too. Other than that you will be rewarded by two snorkeling spots where you may enjoy tropical fish and corals. Then you will serve by buffet lunch (BBQ) and there is an option to order for premium lunch which includes Crabs too. End of the experience, we will drop you back to Boracay beach along the memories grabbed across the day.

fields.title: Small-Group Boat Tour of Charleston Oyster Farm
fields.description:
This tour offers guests an unparalleled opportunity to see exactly where their food comes from in a hyper-local context surrounded by the beauty of the salt marsh. There is no better way to see, taste and experience the bounty of the sea than an oyster farm tour. 

Travellers and locals alike come away with a knowledge, appreciation and hope for the future of our coastal communities that is provided by oysters and the budding industry that's focused on their many benefits to the economy and ecology.

fields.title: Cockle Shell Beach Guided Tour
fields.description:
Your guide is most courteous and knowledgeable, our tour includes brief stops at both Timothy Hill and White House Bay for great photo opportunities and relaxation. You are provided with a complimentary drink on the scenic drive.

You are also provided with a guided introduction to the history of the South East Peninsula and the role it is playing in the island's tourism industry.

At Cockleshell Beach, you can swim, sun bathe, relax or dine at the Spice Mill Restaurant.
