fields.title: 3 Hours Safari Morning or Afternoon By ATV Quad With Camel Ride - Al Quseir
fields.description:
Explore the desert by quad bike on this exciting tour from Marsa Alam. You will be picked up at your hotel and taken to the quad bikes, where you will have the chance to test drive and learn all the important details of the vehicle before setting off on the tour.
Get into gear and conquer the sand dunes. Let the desert flash past you and feel the adrenaline rush through your body. After about an hour you will reach your destination (Bedouin village) .
Here you can relax, drink Bedouin tea, water and experience the Bedouin lifestyle. You can also enjoy a camel ride before heading back through the sand dunes to the starting point.

fields.title: Full Day Private Luxor Tour from Al Quseir
fields.description:
Pickup early in the morning and transfer by air-conditioned coach to Luxor, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, where your guide meets you. First, cross the Nile to the West Bank and the famous Valley of the Kings, with 63 royal tombs dating back almost 4,000 years: The elaborate art that decorates their walls gives an insight into how Egypt’s rulers lived.
Next, visit the Temple of Queen Hatshepsut at Deir el Bahari, a tribute to Egypt’s gender-bending female pharaoh, and the giant statues known as the Colossi of Memnon.
Cross back to the East Bank and relax with a traditional local lunch before you explore the vast Temple of Karnak. Finish with a visit to an alabaster factory before your coach drops you back at your hotel.

fields.title: 3 Hour Buggy Car Safari with Camel Ride and Transfer
fields.description:
Explore the desert by Buggy car on this exciting tour from Marsa Alam.
Get into gear and conquer the sand dunes. Let the desert flash past you and feel the adrenaline rush through your body. After about an hour you will reach your destination (Bedouin village) .
Here you can relax, drink Bedouin tea, water, smoke shisha and experience the Bedouin lifestyle. You can also enjoy a camel ride before heading back through the sand dunes to the starting point

fields.title: Full Day Private Cairo Tour from Al Quseir
fields.description: Travel to Cairo from Marsa Alam on a full-day private tour to make the most of your time in this world-famous city with round-trip private transfers. You'll visit Cairo's most famous sites including the Great Pyramids and Sphinx, once ranked as an Ancient Wonder of the World, and see the spectacular Tutankhamun collection at the Egyptian Museum, including the boy king’s death mask. Witness the best of Egypt’s capital in one unforgettable day. Stop for an included lunch and visit a Papyrus Institute. Enjoy a flexible itinerary and personalized commentary from an Egyptologist guide in Cairo.

fields.title: Full-Day Snorkeling Sea Trip in Coral Garden Amazing with Lunch
fields.description: Coral Gardens was named to be one of the best snorkeling and diving sites. Don't miss the chance to swim in crystal clear water at (Mekky's Room) arriving there by zodiac, after enjoying the amazing snorkeling at Mekkey's room we will move to another wonderful site called (Alam reefs) for snorkeling and possibility to watch dolphins, then having delicious lunch where is the wreck boat. a Real amazing day at one of the most beautiful places you can find in Egypt.

fields.title: Super Moto Marine ATV QUAD, Buggy Car, Snorkeling, Snacks - Al Quseir
fields.description: First you will drive your quad bike for 1 hour to Bedouin village to enjoy visiting a Bedouin tribe and get to know more about their life and traditions. You will also enjoy 15 minutes buggy car , know and enjoy even more the wonderful visions of the desert. Sandwiches is offered to give you power . Enjoy one hour snorkeling with equipment. Finally you will be transferred back to your Hotel.

fields.description:
Explore two of the most famous monuments in Egypt, the UNESCO-listed Abu Simbel temples. Skip

fields.title: Marsa Mubarak Snorkeling and one intro Diving With Lunch, Transfer - Al Quseir
fields.description: Marsa Mubark was named to be one of the best snorkeling & Diving sites. Don't miss the chance to swim in crystal clear water at (Mekky's Room) arriving there by Zodiac, after enjoying the amazing snorkeling at Mekkey's room we will move to another wonderful site called (Alam reefs) for snorkeling & possibility to watch dolphins, then having delicious lunch and moving to the third snorkeling site where is the wreck boat and also you will go diving for 15 minutes with equipment and professional diver. a Real amazing day at one of the most beautiful places you can find in Egypt.

fields.description:

Enjoy lunch served onboard the boat during the trip.

fields.title: Day Trip from Al Quseir to Luxor Kings valley, Hatchepsout, Menmon with Lunch
fields.description:
Expect pickup early in the morning and transfer by air-conditioned coach to Luxor, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, where your guide meets you. First, cross the Nile to the West Bank and the famous Valley of the Kings, with 63 royal tombs dating back almost 4,000 years: The elaborate art that decorates their walls gives an insight into how Egypt’s rulers lived.
Next, visit the Temple of Queen Hatshepsut at Deir el Bahari, a tribute to Egypt’s gender-bending female pharaoh, and the giant statues known as the Colossi of Memnon.
Cross back to the East Bank and relax with a traditional local lunch before you explore the vast Temple of Karnak. Finish with a visit to an alabaster factory before your coach drops you back at your hotel.

fields.title: Al Quseir Safari ATV Quad Sunset, Camel Ride, and Transfer
fields.description:
Discover the vast expanse of the Sahara and the desert mountains. You can then enjoy the thrilling ride through the desert sand. Afterwards you will get in a dune quad and enjoy a very special driving experience.
You will then continue on to a Bedouin village. Enjoy the typical hospitality with Arabic tea and fresh flatbread as you learn more about the traditional life of the Bedouins. You also have the option of taking a camel ride .

fields.title: Boquete Full Adventures
fields.description:
The coffee tour consist in an interpretation about the history, production and process. This coffee tour takes is an small farm where sustainable tourism is practiced.

We are proud to introduce our coffee tour offering the opportunity to taste an excellent cup of SPECIAL coffee. Our coffee tour you will learn all about the coffee process ¨from seed to cup¨.

Our farm obtained second place for the best coffee in Panama and every year we are among the top 10.

It takes about 3 hours and all the processes are artesanal. 

Boquete is famous for its coffee which is known as the most expensive in the world every year. Boquete competes with other countries and Panama is always the first place.

fields.title: Tasting and buying wines in the cellar
fields.description:
Today, white wines have become very similar, regardless of their variety, from the various geographical locations of production. wine is no longer an expression of a territory, of a tradition, of the cellarman's method but has become a drink as banal as a soft drink.
We find it more correct that wines are produced for their positive evolution, which can safely last beyond 10 years. The wines from the cellar that you taste have been produced in this way, which is why none of our wines from last year's harvest have been bottled until September, which you will see on the table only in autumn

fields.title: Wine and Cheese Picnic Cruise on the Seine River
fields.description:
A different way to discover Paris and the Parisian monuments : Along the Seine River, you will enjoy a breathtaking view of the most beautiful monuments, the Institut de France, Notre Dame, the conciergerie, the city hall, the Louvre, the Grand Palais, the Alexander III Bridge, the Statue of Liberty... and of course the Eiffel Tower. Come aboard the drunken boat Maxim's, decorated in the purest Art Nouveau style, and experience the atmosphere of the Belle Epoque on the Seine.
At the end of your cruise, the Captain will gently take you back to 'Bon Port' at the bottom of Notre Dame, all that's left to do is enjoy the quay with why not, one of our bottles of Champagne to take away!

fields.title: Day Experience in High Tatras: Challenge of Porter
fields.description: The porter in High Tatras is the last job in Europe. Carry up the material is challenge for stronger man and woman. You can feeling the freedom under load.

fields.title: Private Tour : Langkawi Island Popular Excursion Packages
fields.description:
Climb aboard the highest cable car ride in all of Malaysia on the Langkawi Skycab Cable Car. The Langkawi Skycab Cable Car is a must-visit attraction in Langkawi whether you’re visiting with friends or family
Hop aboard and visit other attractions including the Skydome, SkyRex, and more!

Ride through the eastern cliffs of Mt. Machinchang and see its lush forests from above. Challenge yourself by opting for a glass-bottom floor gondola and feel the adrenaline as you hop aboard the cable car with one of the steepest slopes in the world

Arrive at Langkawi's second highest peak, Mt. Machinchang, in just a few minutes! Go up 708m above sea level to catch views of Langkawi town, the entire archipelago and Southern Thailand.

Get to try various attractions at the stations such as the Skydome, Sky Bridge, Skyrex, 3D Art Langkawi, and more!

Enjoy fantastic view of langkawi from the Sky Bridge

fields.title: Small Group Guided Shared Tour To Gishora Drum Sanctuary From Bujumbura
fields.description:
Join us on this small group guided tour from Bujumbura City to the famous Gishora Drum Sanctuary. Burundi is known as one of the best African Countries to go to for the real African Drum experience. Gishora Drum Sanctuary is the birthplace of this fascinating cultural and heritage experience. 

Learn how to beat these giant drums and learn how to make dancing moves. Gishora is by far the premier drum sanctuary and the birthplace of the majestic Burundi drummers, an attraction that should be the number one on your Burundi holidays bucket list.

 Sample some best Burundi coffee at Green Park Resort, See tea plantations and Stop at Kibira National Park for sightseeing. Gitega the new Burundi Capital City lunch here for the dishes and organic flavors and visit the National Museum.

See breathtaking scenery as you drive by endless valleys and mountains & see why Burundi is known as the Country of thousand hills with greener landscapes that will leave you breathless. An all-inclusive trip

captions: the best drum dancers in Burundi

fields.title: Krakow: Former Concentration Camp Plaszow Guided Tour
fields.description:
Plashow is a Nazi concentration camp in the southern suburbs of Krakow, founded by the Nazis shortly after the German invasion of Poland. Originally, Plashow, opened in 1940, was planned as a forced labor camp, but in 1941 the camp was expanded and subsequently converted into a concentration camp, where from October 28, 1942, deportation of Jews from the Krakow ghetto began. 
Plashow was known as a concentration camp, supplying several military factories and a quarry with labor. 
The camp and life in it are shown in the Schindler's List movie (1993) about the life of Oskar Schindler. The area which held the camp now consists of sparsely wooded hills and fields, with one large memorial to all the victims, erected in 1964 and few smaller. As the Plaszow area is now a nature preserve, so the director Steven Spielberg built a camp replica in the Liban Quarry, some hundred meters away. We will visit all this points during our tour.

fields.title: Lisbon’s Post-Colonial Feast
fields.description: On this full-day tour, we will explore the complex story of post-colonial Portugal through how it’s expressed in the kitchens of central Lisbon. We’ll start with the signature Cape Verdean stew, cachupa. Packed with hominy, studded with Portuguese chorizo and topped with an egg, the version we’ll try is prepared by the self-proclaimed “King of Cachupa” himself. We’ll have coffee from Angola and chocolate from Sao Tome, learning about these commodities roots in slavery and their current move toward free-trade standards. We’ll visit a shop selling religious icons from Brazil and learn about how African religious traditions were disguised within Catholicism for centuries by colonial subjects of the Portuguese crown.

Ridge scrambling is an exhilarating and hands-on way to experience the Cairngorm mountains. Unlike rock climbing, scrambling is about the journey. We'll select a route that will be challenging but achievable and is big on scenery and satisfaction!

On this immersive experience you'll get to climb one or more historic mountaineering routes; in a remote corrie, along an airy ridge or up sheer cliff face!

This experience is suitable for novices, beginners and travellers looking for a special experience in the local area. No prior experience of climbing or mountaineering is necessary and you'll be kept safe and encouraged every step of the way.

Our guides hold the highest attainable qualifications in mountaineering and climbing and are passionate about giving you the best possible experience. We are as excited guided complete beginners as we are guiding experienced climbers and we enjoy working with both the young and the young at heart... 

We look forward to exploring with you!

fields.title: Macabre Ghost History of Portland, Oregon walking tour: Chills and Chills
fields.description:
From fiery deaths to watery graves: In this 1.5 mile cemetery walking tour, we weave what we know of the peoples who lived here for millennia with verifiable stories of recent centuries. We can only guess, based on our psychics’ readings and eerie coincidences we have observed, where people here before us feared to walk and canoe at night.

As a wise person wrote, every story ends as a ghost story. Our ghosts are legion. 

We now call it Oregon; “ourigan” was ancestral home to hundreds of thousands. They have left a darkness here, expressed with stories from the earliest days of our written history to modern times.

Starting with early disasters, we will tell ghost stories we have collected, from fiery deaths to those in the waters of nearby river; from self-inflicted to deaths brought by the state or a rich man’s guilt. Our route takes us through the inner eastside, where more of Portland’s disasters have happened than any other part of the city & where many early settlers are buried.

captions: The mass graves of Chinese immigrants make for hundreds of troubled spirits
James C. Hawthorne was called a "vampire of the state" by his critics
The former high school burned on a waxing crescent moon in 1922
the grave of baby Elk, one of many young residents at Lone Fir cemetery
Ice cream, you scream... we'll stop for some of the city's best ice cream at the end of the tour

You will have the chance to take the cable car to reach the bay of Taormina and see Isola Bella, which is a protected natural site as well as a beautiful beach.
The driver will pick you up from the bay or the centre at the agreed time to take you back to your cruise.

fields.title: Private Upper Loop Grand Teton, Lower Loop Scenic & Wildlife 3 Day Tours
fields.description:
MAMMOTH HOT SPRINGS AND LAMAR VALLEY stand out in the upper loop of Yellowstone, because of their volcanic and glaciation history. Every hundred years or so, the hot springs migrate from one spot to another and always leave behind calcium carbonate. You could hike up the travertine terraces. Sometimes elk hang out in the village unafraid of people.

Lamar Valley could have been carved out by glaciers thousands of years ago. Now what is left behind is boulders that must have also been moved by glaciers. You will see them strewn around before you get to Lamar Valley proper. The soil in Lamar is suitable for lush grass that you will see. And that attracts bison, pronghorn, elk. But it also attracts wolves and Grizzlies that want to have the other animals previously mentioned for meal.

Besides these two attractions, you will also see Tower Falls as well as Calcite Springs which oozes with super hot sulfuric oil. With time left, we shall take you to the petrified tree.

fields.title: Private Tour in Grand Teton National Park and Yellowstone Lower Loop
fields.description:
GRAND TETON, YELLOWSTONE WILDLIFE, SCENIC, HISTORY TOURS. On this epic two day tour of the two parks, you could see moose, bison, elk, mule deer, pronghorn, black bears, Grizzlies, wolves, swans, bald eagles, foxes, coyotes. We will present a brief settlement history of Jackson Hole, as well as geology, scenic tours. We shall hike to Hidden Falls. Stops in the Tetons include Signal Mountain and several other historic and scenic stops. 
 The approach is the same in Yellowstone. However, we shall touch on the brief history of the super volcano of Yellowstone, that way you will have a better understanding of why you will see fumaroles, geysers, hot springs and mud pots. Tours include Old Faithful, Grand Prismatic Spring, Waterfalls at the Artist Point, wildlife watching in Hayden Valley, the mud volcano and Lake Yellowstone.

This is a group tour, so you might make some new friends as you go along. We provide land transfer within city area as well. fields.title: 2 Day Nature Tour in Tam Giang Lagoon & Bach Ma National Park
fields.description:
For those who is a nature lover, Tam Giang – Cau Hai Lagoon and Bach Ma National park are the gems of Hue.
Tam Giang – Cau Hai Lagoon is located at the merge of three big rivers including O Lau, Huong and Bo Rivers. It is the largest freshwater lagoon system in Hue. 
A French-era hill station, Bach Ma national park reaches a peak of 1450m at Bach Ma mountain. The cool climate attracted the French, who built over a hundred villas here during the colonial period in the early 1930s. A mountainous area not far from the coast, Bach Ma not only has atmospheric jungle and interesting flora & fauna but also spectacular views over the beautiful coastal beaches and Tam Giang –Cau Hai lagoon. Furthermore, Bach Ma is not on the popular tourist route so you are likely to enjoy this natural wonder away from the crowds.
This adventure/ecological tour will take you to the most unique and beautiful landscapes around Hue city, Central Vietnam.

captions: Panoramic view from top of Bach Ma peak to Tam Giang - Cau Hai Lagoon

The tour offers you the opportunity to see the best of Morocco in just 3 days and see the barbary Macacos in Azrou, take a sightseeing desert tour see nomads living in caves, visit the donkey market in Risani, wander with a local guide in palmary or hike in Dades valley or Todra gorges, spend more time of sites, share a cup of tea with a Berber family...Etc.

fields.title: Private Discovery of the Hidden Paris Behind the Bastille and its Revolutions
fields.description:
The Bastille! Which Bastille? Where is the Bastille? And what is this column in the middle of the square? What about that strange vessel with glass facades? Follow us and dive in the heart of the French revolutions on the Bastille and through the faubourg Saint-Antoine district!
From the ‘Colonne de Juillet’ to the Aligre market and its lively shops, from the shadows of narrow passageways to the surprising working-class courtyards, come and take a look at the discreet district of the Quinze-Vingts, with its often overlooked corners. The district, however, is one of the most dynamic and certainly of the most important in the history of Paris! Human revolutions, of course, but also industrial revolutions have left their marks here, which your steps will lead you to! So don't be surprised if this unusual guided tour of the former "furniture district" have you discover an elephant never really fitted the room or black musketeers playing dice in a hidden courtyard!

We will pick you up from your Hotel in Hurghada in an air-conditioned bus to Luxor, the land of Civilization. 

After that, you can relax over lunch at a local restaurant and enjoy one of the traditional dishes of Luxor.

Then get on board a Felucca, a type of sailing boat that has been used since the Pharaohs, across the Nile to the City of the Dead (optional). The impressive Colossi of Memnon will greet you there – the last remnants of the Temple of Amenophis III.

Be enthralled by the magnificent architecture of the Valley of the Queens and visit the temple of Hatshepsut, one of the female rulers of Ancient Egypt. And after you've had enough time to explore the extensive monuments to your satisfaction, you will be driven back to your hotel.

fields.title: Full-day 4x4 Jeep Tour in Wadi Rum Desert

We offer a unique and personal Jeep Tour experience by our Team of knowledgeable Bedouin Guides. You will not only experience the traditional Bedouin hospitality you have never experienced before, but we will also make real Wadi Rum experts out of you by preparing you with all kinds of information about our lifestyle, our tradition and surely about the Desert. Wadi Rum is one of the world's most beautiful deserts. More than just a sea of rolling dunes, this protected wilderness near Jordan's southern border is made unique by the dramatic sandstone and basalt mountains jutting out of its sandy floor. Named "The Valley of the Moon" for good reason, the area's natural intrigue is endless: stunning rock formations, fascinating rock art, and a brilliant night sky combine to create a unique and worthwhile destination. Contact our team and start planning your perfect trip.

fields.title: Shore Excursion Guided Tour From Casablanca Port to Marrakech

After 3 hours driving, you will enjoy the rest day exploring this enchanting city, known as Morocco’s ‘pearl of the south’. The historical sightseeing includes Menara Garden, Koutoubia Mosque, Bahia Palace and Si Said Museum.visit the souks and handicraft quarters in the afternoon to go shopping. End the day at the famous Djemâa El Fina before returning to your cruise ship in Casablanca port. The tour will last around 12 hours, returning you to your ship in Casablanca in the evening.

fields.description: Spend a day out on the water with a snorkeling trip from Sharm el Sheikh in a Luxury Sailing Boat. Take advantage of the marvelous warm weather in Sharm el Sheikh with a full-day out on the Red Sea. Travel by boat out to the Red Sea Coral Reefs under water islands, where you will spend a relaxing day snorkeling, exploring the islands, and enjoying a lavish Sea Food & Grill buffet lunch on the boat.

fields.description: Bike is the most libertarian mean of transportation and probably the best way to explore new places. In 4 hours, you will be able to discover all sides of Athens city. You can have any infos from a local and after this bike tour you will be much more familiar with the city. If you visit Athens for first time and you like cycling, this is a must to do.

fields.title: Hike for cave experience under the stars in Wadi Rum
fields.description:
Off the beaten track and out of the hard camps, come and live a unique experience.

The best way to appreciate the beauty of the Wadi Rum desert. A desert that was millions of years ago submerged by the sea. A desert where poetry ricochets between the cliffs like the sound of stones or sand rising up.

The Bedouin tradition, which persists in this desert from century to century, is inscribed through nomadic life. This tour will allow you to immerse yourself in the history of these canyons and hidden trails with a local guide.

You will discover why Wadi Rum is divided into two deserts, what are the so-called mushroom rocks, what is the meaning of the Petroglyphs engraved by the Nabateans who had already started to tame this desert 13 centuries before us.

Far away from all of the non natural light, the cave experience is the best way to enjoy the colors of the sun set and sun rise. From our caves we will be able to see a sky full of stars and the milky way.

اهلا وسهلا في وادي رم

fields.title: Hardangerfjord and Fyksesund RIB safari from Norheimsund
fields.description:
Across the Hardangerfjord, the trip enters the old trading town of Herandsholmen. From here the trips goes north across the fjord and enters Fyksesund which is an adventurous beautiful fjord arm midway through the Hardangerfjord.

Fyksesund is the only side fjord in the Hardangerfjord without a road to the inner part of the fjord arm. The last 5 km of the 10 km long fjord goes between steep mountainsides to the roadless old village Botnen at the end of the fjord.

Join us on an adrenaline-filled RIB tour – the fastest boat ride you can get! Your driver and guide stops a couple of times to let the unique scenery work its magic and to provide interesting facts about the fjord and people who used to live at the fjord farms. With a bit of luck even porpoises show themselves in the water.

There are several stops close to land along the way to experience nature and life along the fjord. It is important to have a camera easily accessible.

fields.title: 2 Day Tour to Mountain (Juta and Kazbegi) with Horse Riding

Enjoy the breathtaking views, touch nature, visit one of the highest inhabited village in Europe Juta (2200 meters from the sea level), ride horses accompanied by the local followers who hold the horses. Our qualified trekking guide will lead you to Gveleti waterfall and will take care of your safety and satisfaction.

fields.title: Private Market Tour and Cooking Class with Lunch or Dinner in Cervia
fields.description:
Dive into the Italian way of life by living just like the locals do.

Visit the vibrant local market and the traditional food shops with the Cesarina and immerse yourself in a private cooking class at the Cesarina's home, learn the secrets of the most famous dishes of local cuisine and taste the fruit of your labour accompanied by a glass of local wine.

During the lesson the Cesarina will reveal the tricks of the trade of 3 authentic regional recipes. Have fun putting your cooking skills to the test. During this private hands-on cooking class you will have a workstation equipped with utensils and all the ingredients to make the dishes. Then, taste everything you have prepared accompanied by a selection of local wines.

Le Cesarine is Italy’s oldest network of 600+ home cooks all over the country in more than 120 cities. They are passionate and welcoming hosts that open the doors of their own homes to curious travellers for immersive culinary experiences.

fields.title: Full guided day tour of Ubud with experienced local and couchsurfer host
fields.description: Travel with a 16 year local of Bali as well as a regular couchsurfing host in a comfy air conditioned vehicle visiting the sites at a leisurely pace

fields.title: U PRISC, Dinner with the authentic Flavours of Puglia
fields.description:
In the host dialect, "u prisc" indicates the joy in doing something, the same joy Mauro and you will feel in sharing this journey to discover the ancient traditional flavors from Apulia.
The food is cooked in an old stone oven of the wood-fired farmhouse dating back to 1700 so the food that will taste originate from the most ancient peasant traditions of Apulia. All the dishes will be cooked in traditional terracotta pans following ancient family recipes.
The dinner will take place in the most beautiful and oldest area of ​​the farm: the stables, with the authentic mangers and the original stone flooring.

fields.title: Exclusive Private Sailboat Tour on the Amalfi Coast
fields.description: A Private tour where the flexibility and availability of the staff will make the experience even more exclusive. In addition to the enchanting places to visit along the Divina Costa, with the help of the wind you can feel the silence and the emotion of the sea that only the Sailboat can give you.

fields.title: Porto: Walking Tour + Six Bridges River Cruise
fields.description:
With this pass, discover the best of Porto on a guided walking tour and a six bridges river cruise!

Embark the popular river cruise and set sail along the Douro River, admiring Porto's colourful landscape and eye-catching architecture. You will see the famous six bridges, including the D. Luís Bridge and Infante Bridge, that have become Porto's most treasured and recognised landmarks. You will also hear how the cruises were once used to transport porto wine from the Douro Valley, therefore playing an important role in Porto's famous gastronomy scene. 

Continue your exploration through the city, which was coined an UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1996. Learn all about Porto's rich heritage from your tour guide, as you stroll past many famous landmarks such as the Torre dos Clérigos, Mercado Ferreira Borges and Jardim do Morro. Admire the city's fascinating contrast of cobbled streets and rich architecture, before enjoying sweeping views of the Douro River.

fields.title: Best of Miami with Cruise Port Pick-up and Airport Drop-off
fields.description: Experience the Best of Miami, starting at the Port of Miami, on this 5-hour small group tour of the Magic City. Explore the city's vibrant Cuban heart - Little Havana, experience the beauty of Wynwood Walls, and relax on a cruise in the harbor among others.

Electric Fat Bike Tour to Tegallalang Rice Fields, to experience the ride through villages, visit village temples, see the traditional houses, and visit the one of the best rice terrace in with their subak irigation system, where that system has been "World Heritage by UNESCO".

 Our guide will not only guide you to visit the most beautiful places in Ubud, but they will also give you explanation about the places you visited.

Tour Itenary

You will walk among the volcanic lava and you will wash tiny as you see the impressive environment declared a World Heritage Site by UNESCO The P. N. del Teide is located in the center of the island, at an average altitude of 2,000 meters.

fields.title: Half-Day Sunrise Tour in Marrakech Hot Air Balloon Flight
fields.description:
A little before the first light of day, you will arrive at our take-off base where we will warmly welcome you with a small snack (tea, coffee, cookies). The hot air balloons will already be in preparation so you can take the opportunity to take photos and videos. Take-off is imminent! You will then embark in the basket to watch the sunrise at 1000m. The show is unique and magical, in a monastic silence (apart from the intermittent noise of the burners) you can observe the surrounding mountains and the High Atlas. Part of the flight will also take place at a lower altitude, which will give you the feeling of being on a magic carpet.
On the program + 3 hours of service: Pick up in front of your place of residence; Reception and safety briefing; Flight (45 to 60 min); Landing and return to flight base; Traditional Berber breakfast; Delivery of baptismal certificates; Departure for your place of residence

See you very soon in the air!

fields.title: Marrakech Quad Biking with Camel ride
fields.description:
Hotel picks up and drop off included and you will definitely experience the rush of excitement on an adventure trip that departs from Marrakech and allows you to participate in two activities in a lush oasis located on the outskirts of the city. Experience the terrain on a camel while riding through the Palmeraie on a quad bike.

You will experience the following highlights:
- Travel on a camel across the oasis of Marrakech's palm grove on the outskirts of the city.
- Quad bike your way across the rough terrain of the Moroccan countryside.
- Mint tea and snacks are waiting for you with a Berber family.

fields.title: Marrakech City Tour
fields.description:
We will pick you up at your accommodation in Marrakech and start the exciting city tour with you.
First you'll visit the Koutoubia Mosque which is the largest mosque in Marrakesh, then we will visit the Bahia Palace where we can admire Its fantastic architecture as well as its shady courtyards and impressive mosaic walls.
We walk through the old medina of Marrakech and its old market "Souk" where you are going to see the way of life of local people and smell the different spices learning about trendy Argan oil in a specialty store.
We will also visit The Ben Youssef Madrasa is an Islamic madrasa (college) in Marrakesh, Functioning today as a historical site, the Ben Youssef Madrasa was the largest Islamic college in Morocco at its height.
We will Explore the green side of Marrakech in a fun way stroll through the impressive Majorelle Garden in the new city to admire its beauty and its fantastic complexes.
Tour and sights can be changed based on your individual choices.

fields.title: 8 Days Camel Trek at the Desert in Morocco
fields.description: Camel Trek 8 Days To Erg Chigaga. The Desert Hike in Morocco is a walk in the big dunes of southern Morocco with a professional nomadic guide and camel drivers. A camel caravan carries the luggage. The fascination of desert immensities, an unusual encounter with nomads, study and observation of animal and plant life, relaxation, silence, and total forgetfulness of civilization and the modern world in absolute calm in the heart of the great desert of the Moroccan Sahara, at sunrise and unforgettable sunsets. During the hike, you live according to the rhythm and the intensity of the sun, everyone advances at his pace accompanied by the camel drivers.

fields.title: 3-Day Private Erg Chigaga Sahara Desert Tour from Marrakech

This desert tour provides you with the opportunity to make priceless memories in a great number of spectacular locations that are each worthy of being seen at least once in one's lifetime. 

Explore amazing locations including Ouarzazate, Draa Valley, Merzouga dunes, Iriki Lake, Atlas mountains, Ait Benhaddou Kasbah, Draa Valley, Tichka pass, Kasbah of Telouet, and so on.

fields.title: Group Boat Snorkeling and BBQ Lunch on Board in Aqaba
fields.description: We offer you the opportunity to snorkel on board in the middle Red sea of Aqaba to explore the wonders of the aquatic life. The Red Sea is well-known for its beautiful coral reefs and is one of the most popular diving destinations in the world due to its exceptional visibility and pure water. We provide you with up-to-date gears, fitted suits and responsible professional guides along your trip to enjoy a safe and exciting tour. We will also make sure to document all your magical underwater moments with digital photos and videos taken with our high resolution cameras. This trip is appropriate for all skill levels and ages. Children over the age of 5 are invited to participate, and swimming abilities are not necessary. If necessary, we will provide you with life jackets. fields.title: Sun City Ghosts Haunted Cowboys and Outlaws Tour
fields.description:
Googling the history is an option, but what fun is that? For a trip back in time that includes visits to places of historical significance and stories that didn’t make the history book, what better way than a tour with Sun City Ghosts? 

The role Texas played in the formation of the United States is a major one, so it’s easy to see why it’s shrouded in deep history that is both monumental and otherworldly.

This isn’t like any history lesson you’ve ever slept through. Educational and engaging, this tour will take you on a trip through centuries of history and hauntings. Texas history includes so much more than we were taught in school, and Sun City Ghosts is where you’ll hear it.

These aren’t your run-of-the-mill ghost stories that you’ll hear. Our research team has uncovered terrifying true accounts of unexplained activity that range from spirit sightings to inexplicable voices and sounds to being touched by unidentified beings.

Additional Information on horse riding tours:

Some riding experience is recommended as there are several areas where you may be required to dismount and walk the horse and then mount the horse again to continue the tour. fields.title: Tombstone - Boothill and San Xavier Del Bac Private Tour

This day tour gives you the chance to venture south from the Phoenix area to see several historical sites that visitors come from around the world to see. This allows you to experience several interesting locations that are so important in the history of Arizona. 

Our first stop will be at the Mission at San Xavier del Bac where you will have a chance to learn more about the area south of Tucson and see the detail and wonderful architecture of the church, built 100's of years ago. Then off to Tombstone which is such a unique experience to see and be able to walk in the same steps as Wyatt Earp, Doc Holliday and the Clantons. 

The shopping is very unique and interesting, and the towns people all dress in period outfits. While in town we will see a Shootout at the OK Corral and have lunch (included up to $15 per person) on the old main street of town. We have one final stop at the Boothill Graveyard to visit the graves of many of Tombstone famous citizens. Then it's back to Phoenix.

fields.title: Moonee Ponds Trail
fields.description:
Located just 7km from Melbourne CBD, Moonee Ponds has some great streets to discover. Century-old churches, historic dwellings, and parks line the street. Fine restaurants and sports bars are also a common sight in the Moonee Ponds area. Puckle Street is always buzzing, it’s a shopping strip that appears to have something for everybody.

With a selection of some of the best thrift shops, restaurants, bars, and cafes. From freshest Japanese to authentic Lebanese to European tapas on this adventure we get to meet the local business owners, share their stories and get to know the unique businesses of the area. The locals say “ if you don’t want to leave Moonee Ponds you don’t have to.”

From there, choose an ocean-bound adventure, sip cocktails in the Atlantic, snorkel the reefs, or party at the sandbar. Feeling hungry? Take your journey to a waterfront restaurant or take advantage of our catering options. Our luxurious vessel is equipped with complimentary snacks, towels, floats, ice-cold water, and available snorkel equipment. If we're missing something, make a list and our concierge service will have it ready to go before departure. Our large cabin fits two bedrooms, two bathrooms, showers, a storage room for luggage, and a comfortable entertainment center. Perfect for any day or evening excursion, our crew is ready to build your perfect getaway.

fields.title: Self-Guided Shared Tour From Katakolon to Olympia
fields.description:
Enjoy a shore excursion to the popular cruise destination Ancient Olympia.
Discover the birthplace of the Olympic Games on this 3hours 30minutes self-guided shore excursion from Katakolo. Upon debarkation, please proceed through the cruise terminal and exit through the security area. You can easily locate our office 30 meters away from the main exit of the port, on your left. We will assist you to issue your pre-booked tickets and reserve your seats. The tour starts approx. 1-1 ½ hrs after the ship’s arrival to the port. Embark on a fully air-conditioned coach with our professional drivers to start your memorable journey through the picturesque lands of Ilia, as you reach Olympia.
After arriving at Olympia, you are dropped off at the parking area, just 100m away from the entrance of the Archeological Site of Olympia.
At the end of the tour, you get dropped off back at your cruise terminal in time for your ship departure.

fields.title: Half-Day Walking Tour to Infamous Third Reich Sites in Berlin
fields.description:
Gain insight into Berlin's Nazi past on this 4-hour walking tour of the infamous Third Reich sites. Accompanied by a historian guide, walk to the ruins of Anhalter Bahnhof, used to deport prisoners to concentrations camps, and see the former Gestapo and SS headquarters and the site of Hitler's bunker. Learn about those who struggled against the Nazi system of terror, and get a fuller, deeper look at the haunting realities of the Holocaust. Your tour will finish before the German parliament building, the Reichstag.

This is a half-day tour, and the remaining time will depend on the travelers. We can stay longer at 1 attraction depending on the travelers' interest.

fields.title: Cracow in 2 hours - Old Town Guided Walking tour
fields.description:
Cracow has a lot to offer and absolute must see is located in the heart of it, which is essential as a first step.
Walk around the very many cobbled streets of the UNESCO listed old town, where we talk about the history of the city, our kings and the queen and local stories about us - Poles.
If you’d like to get to know Polish history in a nutshell - this one’s for you. Back in the 15th and 16th century, Kraków was one of the best-developed and richest cities in Europe. Luckily enough, most of it remained untouched despite turbulent and, sometimes, even tragic history.

The sights you will see on this tour are impossible to describe without using superlatives - the biggest market square in medieval Europe, the oldest university building in the world still in use, one of the oldest souvenir shops, the best-preserved medieval altar… The list goes on and on.

fields.title: Private Traditional Sri Lankan Cooking Class in Colombo
fields.description: Enjoy a private and authentic Sri Lankan meal with your host Bandu in his home. This is a perfect experience for anyone looking to connect with local culture over food. Bandu is a kind and friendly host, a retired IT professional who has lived overseas for over 35 years. He learned to cook from his mother and has been cooking traditional, home style Sri Lankan food for over 40 years. He initially learned to cook for survival as a young professional and now is extremely passionate about cooking for friends. Apart from cooking, Bandu likes traveling, hiking and swimming. He has traveled to over 35 countries and has even learned to cook local food in a few of them. When asked why he would like to be a host, Bandu says, “this is a great opportunity to learn about other cultures and meet like-minded people.”

fields.title: Berlengas Catamaran Tour
fields.description:
Enjoy a different day on this 3 to 4h mini cruise where we will take you to see extreme beauty places along the coast of Peniche, to know (via App Odisseia Viva) the stories of the political prison, shipwrecks, and pirate attacks.

Upon arriving at the island you can walk the trails; take a boat tour of the caves; visit Fort St. John, the Baptist, or the Duke of Bragança Lighthouse.

The Berlengas archipelago is a group of small islands located 5.7 miles off the coast of Peniche and comprises Berlenga, Estelas, and Farilhões islands. Berlenga is the only inhabited island. In 2011 UNESCO classified the Berlengas as a “World Biosphere Reserve”, which is indicative of the rich fauna and flora that can be found on the islands.
Very often dolphins come to pay us a visit and swim by boat!

fields.title: Uyuni Salt Flat Tour 1 day | English Speaking Guide | Private Service |
fields.description:
We will begin our tour in the 4x4 vehicle destined for the occasion.
The first stop will be the train cemetery, a must for those who visit Uyuni and which is a record of how prosperous the area was. Later, we will move to Colchani, where we can see and buy handicrafts, as well as see how the process of making products from salt is.
Once inside the salt flat, we will visit the monument to the Dakar, the Salt Museum and the Incahuasi island that is right in the middle of the salar. There, we can take a short walk to the highest part and take advantage of the view of the salt flat in 360 °. Also, we can see from very close the large cactus that adorn this calcareous rock formation.
After this experience, we will have our lunch and we will settle to see the sunset in the salar, a true spectacle of nature. Later, we will return in our vehicle to finish the tour.

fields.title: Walk along the Bagmati River (16 heritage monuments in 2 kilometers)
fields.description: Visit 16 heritage monuments in just 2 kilometers walk along Bagmati River. Bagmati River is mother River that bred Nepal’s civilization. At the moment, the river looks like a natural drain instead of the babbling river. Along the walk, see Akhadas (school for shadus and Hindu saints), temples, local houses, day to day local people activities, Sattal (temporary shelter for Pilgrimages). In this short walk, you would visit Kalmochan Temple, Tripura Sundari, Chandra ghat (a place at the edge of a river where Hindus cremate dead people), Purneshwor temple, Puret ghat, Hanuman ghat, Tin dewal, Pachali Bhairav, Laxmeshwor temple, and suspension bridge over Bagmati River, Radha Krishna temple, Teku dovan and Jaganath temple.

fields.title: Private Secret London Walking Tour
fields.description:
Lost love, haunting memories, moving reflection and glimmers of joy - London's raw soul lies under her surface. This private tour will take you deep into our city's hidden world. There are secret parks – the lungs of London, ancient alleys and winding stairways, nestled courtyards, a buried amphitheatre, forgotten markets and apparitions. 

Walking the city's oldest streets – crossing Roman thoroughfares and Mediaeval marketplaces, your guide will share the stories of some of London's famous characters and legends - from Charles Dickens to the Great Fire of London, from Sweeney Todd to Jack the Ripper. 

Discover uncharted passions around every corner as we cross over plague pit burial grounds, touch a 2,000-year-old Roman wall, explore a gorgeous tea shop, a dried-up river, beautiful hidden churches and an undiscovered city waiting to reveal its epic and haunting past. Come and experience a London few know exist and take a journey with us into what lies beneath.

fields.description:
Our Safari itineraries are all about you and your experience. Each itinerary has been thoughtfully designed to ensure that our guests get the very best out of their experience. All of our Overnight Safaris are privately guided by Kruger National Park expert Andrew Wagner who is a qualified Field Guide, Trails Guide and Regional birding specialist. 

Our Central grasslands Safari in the Kruger National Park offers you the quintessential view of vast open African savanna with endless views of plains game and the possibilities of having great Lion sightings. You will Overnight INSIDE the Park and venture into vast Grasslands which focuses on the regions excellent mammal diversity as well as birding and photographic opportunities. This Safari takes you through 4 unique eco-zones that showcase Kruger’s expansive diversity from the Sabie River all the way up to the Olifant's River. 3 days offers just enough time to explore Kruger and make incredible memories.

There is no better experience!

Well Plan Trekking . has knitted the updated itinerary for the Annapurna region’s trekking in Nepal. Annapurna Base Camp Trek in Nepal has many trailheads. We opt for the best and updated route of
trekking 11 Days of trekking is new and unique to us. Our travel planners themselves visited the trail before finalizing the itinerary. The route involves Nepal’s model village Ghandruk as well. The first notable excursion will be among the Gurung and Dalits community. Relish the mountain vistas as well as the cultural grandeurs of hilly Gurung community. The chill breeze of the air coming out of Mt. Annapurna will dazzle your soul. In fact, the trip is the soul enchantment experience as well.

fields.title: Indonesian Traditional Batik Class
fields.description:
Batik is one of the most unique and beautiful things you can get from Indonesia.

Please wear clothes that you don't mind getting a bit of paint on, because this is a hands-on activity, although I'll provide aprons. Be ready to have fun!

fields.title: Private Tour to Sinharaja Rain Forest From Colombo.
fields.description: Sinnharaja Forest Reserve is a national park and a biodiversity hotspot in Sri Lanka. It is of international significance and has been designated a Biosphere Reserve and World Heritage Site by UNESCO.The trip starts at 5 am from Colombo and will take 3 hours to reach the entrance of Sinharaja Rain Forest. You can decide on how far you are going to walk inside the jungle depending on your capacity.

fields.title: Private Photo Session with a Local Photographer in Protaras
fields.description:
Want to capture your amazing honeymoon? Family vacation while the kids are still little? Your perfect couples retreat from everyday busy life? A solo trip without asking strangers to take pictures of you? Stop searching, we got you here!
We are the largest network of local vacation photographers in the world! Besides Protaras, we operate in over 700 destinations worldwide! We always make sure that every special moment of each client is captured well. 
We believe in our service and quality of our photos so much that we even offer a 100% money back satisfaction guarantee for your photo shoot. Which means, if you don’t like the result of your photo shoot, you can contact us within 7 days and claim your money back!
So what are you waiting for? Become one of our hundreds of happy customers by treating yourself to this special experience! Your family and friends will love the result too!

fields.title: Departure Private Transfers from Gothenburg City to Gothenburg Airport GOT
fields.description: Gothenburg Airport Transfer Service aims to achieve the very highest possible standards possible for all its passengers. This is a one-way transfer and includes up to twenty minutes of free waiting time for guests. One of our professionally-trained drivers will greet you with a name sign in the reception of the hotel, ready to help you with your luggage and guide you to your vehicle to go Gothenburg Airport GOT. Traveling from your Hotel to airport with family or colleagues? A Business Car can be shared by up to 3 people together.

Airport Private Transfer in Business Car

fields.title: Sigiriya & Dambulla Day Tour
fields.description:
Sigiriya is most probably one of Sri Lanka’s most iconic site located 15 km northeast of Dambulla. Sigiriya Rock Fortress is located on a flat surface of a gigantic gneiss rock that towers dramatically. Its vertical walls rises up forming a kingdom of Kassapa where now only the ruins of an ancient civilisation exist. In addition, in order to get there, if you are brave enough, you will have to climb a series of staircases that are attached to rock walls.Once you enter the fort, you will get to witness the ruins, frescoes and water gardens around the premises and the sight of the magnificent rolling hills and forest from the fort will simply baffle you.
The beautiful Royal Rock Temple complex sits about 160m above the road in the southern part of Dambulla. Five separate caves contain about 150 absolutely stunning Buddha statues and paintings,some of Sri Lanka&'s most important and evocative religious art. Buddha images were first created here over 2000 years ago.

fields.title: Overnight Agra Tour by Car From Delhi
fields.description: This 2-day private tour of Agra takes you round-trip from Delhi. The comprehensive itinerary includes entrance fees to the UNESCO-listed Taj Mahal and Agra Fort, plus the fortified ancient city of Fatehpur Sikri, so there’s no need to wait in line for tickets to these popular attractions. You’ll have the services of a personal guide and private vehicle transport.

Our small group tours of 16 guests or less make for a fun, family style experience. Snorkel remote, beginner friendly snorkel spots on Maui and Lanai! Snorkel instruction included! Encounter dolphins eye-level on our low-to-water adventure raft vessels! Join us for an ocean rafting adventure you won’t forget!
